225976587597748.description:
RSVP for free via Eventbrite:
http://404day.eventbrite.com/?aff=efbevent

Two decades ago Congress began publishing on the Internet, revolutionizing public access to legislative information. While the technology we use has evolved since the 90s, Congress has not always kept up.

In the meantime, public-minded entrepreneurs have used congressional data to alert people to important bills, keep track of votes, and put citizens in contact with their elected representatives.

While some modernization has occurred, further improvements to Congress’s publishing methods are urgently needed. And with the looming switch from THOMAS to Congress.gov, many organizations and individuals who depend on the available data will be left in the dark, endangering the public’s ability see what its government is doing.

Join our panel of data experts for a discussion of how far we have come, and how far we have yet to go, to fulfill the promise of lawmaking in the open.

 

Keep the conversation going at our evening reception: http://404reception.eventbrite.com

 

Featuring:

Jim Harper, Global Policy Counsel, Bitcoin Foundation; Senior Fellow, Cato Institute (Moderator)

Steve Dwyer, Digital Director & Policy Advisor to Rep. Steny Hoyer

Josh Tauberer, Founder, Govtrack.Us

Nick Schaper, Senior Vice President, Engage

Kirsten Gullickson, Senior Systems Analyst, Clerk of the House of Representatives

 

Learn more about the coalition: www.congressionaldata.org 

Hill credentials are not a requirement for attendance. This event is sponsored by the R Street Institute and CREW, as well as other members of the Congressional Data Coalition.
225976587597748.location: Longworth House Office Building, Room 1310 , Washington, DC, US
225976587597748.name: 4/04 Day: Lawmaking in the Open

226139807553184.description:
Please join us Friday, Dec 5th for one of DC's Greatest New Traditions...  

The 3nd Annual DC Krampusnacht!

With the holidays now upon us, we're all familiar w/ the story of Santa Claus. But according to ancient lore, St. Nicholas actually had several attendants, one of which was the horned satyr Krampus. Whereas St. Nick would reward good little girls & boys, Krampus would punish the bad kids. For 'truly' bad children, he'd even carry them off to later be devoured as his X-mas dinner!  

Traditionally, Kampsuslauf takes place on Dec 5th (day before St. Nicholas Day). Celebratory revelers parade through the night, carousing their way through the streets & warn attendant children to be nice. 

In a city known for its cultural diversity & multinational intrigue, this year we're proud to host the 3rd Annual Kampuslauf on H Street. With a schedule of events that run throughout the evening, Kampusnacht offers a little something for everyone - perfect for families & revelers alike!  


- For a more detailed history see Wikipedia: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Krampus 
- For an idea as to the Krampuslauf Tradition see: www.youtube.com/watch?v=WLnl5ZWG4tg 

All parties are welcome to join in the fun! Full or partial participation is DEEPLY encouraged.  For the parade, any reasonable attempt for authentic costumes (professional or amateur) shall be openly welcome.

 To join the parade, costumes are required - join our group to participate! https://www.facebook.com/groups/krampusnachtdc/

All efforts go to benefit 'Santa's Cause DC' (https://www.facebook.com/SantasCauseDc): a special project for "Family Matters of Washington, DC" - striving to enhance the lives of foster children throughout the DC area, they provide a program for personalized gifts both during the December holidays (delivered by Santa himself) as well as on birthdays. In addition, they provide needed supplies for the entire school year. We will be accepting unwrapped toys & monetary donations to benefit this most worthy cause. 

So bring your family or friends & kick off the holidays with a fun filled evening for all! No Doubt, THIS is a night you won't want to miss!
226139807553184.name: KRAMPUSNACHT DC 2014

228333404037038.description:
2ND ANNUAL BROCCOLI CITY FESTIVAL GOES BI-COASTAL FEATURING CAM'RON, JOJO, VASHTIE, DIZZY WRIGHT, JUST BLAZE, & MORE

Last year, nearly 5,000 people took part in the festivities! Attendees will have access to a pop up marketplace featuring cool and diverse vendors, group yoga and fitness instruction, on-site acupuncture, reikei, massages, live art instillations, sneaker cycling center, and the opportunity to join us for a 5K run.

“BC Fest promotes living a healthier and more environmentally sustainable lifestyle through cool and relevant campaigns,” said Brandon McEachern, Co-Founder of Broccoli City. The campaigns are built on a platform of change and transcendence with the hope to engage and unify a melting pot of cultures in city communities. “Our message is particularly resonant in the political and entertainment capitals of the world, where BC Fest educates future leaders on making informed decisions about their health and environment,” McEachern added.

Working alongside noted causes and organizations such as Earth Day Network, DC Department of Environment (DDOE), DC Sustainability Energy Utility (DCSEU), Los Angeles Office of Sustainability, the White House Initiative on Educational Excellence for African Americans, 72 and Sunny, Zambezi, One Love Massive and Hip Hop Caucus, BC Fest will give the public a fresh look into environmental wellness programs and strategies in a fun setting.

To ensure a low carbon footprint, BC Fest will utilize several sustainable resources, including a LEED Gold certified pavilion in Washington, DC and a solar powered stage in Los Angeles. To remain carbon neutral all of the energy consumed will be offset by renewable energy credits.


For more information, please visit www.BCfestival.com. Attendees are strongly encouraged to purchase tickets in advance to receive a discount and guarantee admission, while supplies last. The festival will commence from noon to 8 p.m., rain or shine.

Founded in 2008 by singer/songwriter Justin Trawick, "The 9 Songwriter Series" is a touring songwriter collective and live show based in Washington, DC. The show was created with the idea of nine artists getting together and combining their talents in order to play in nicer clubs and to larger amounts of people. Each installment features nine solo singer/songwriters performing together in a unique and captivating format, telling stories, and often sitting in each each other and making up music on the spot. Where else can you hear almost 30 songs from nine different artists in one evening and often for only $10? To date, over 200 different artists have participated in "The 9", at shows in DC, Baltimore, Annapolis, Philadelphia, New York, Fairfield, Boston, Richmond, Charlottesville, Charlotte, Atlanta, Los Angeles and San Francisco.

Follow and Like "The 9" at www.twitter.com/wearethe9 and www.facebook.com/wearethe9. Watch the promo video by visiting www.wearethe9.com.

234197360117781.description:
Come to our April "Why I Believe" Fireside featuring Brother and Sister Gillespie, current missionaries in the Washington D.C. Temple Visitors' Center. The fireside will be held on Sunday, March 16, 2013 at 7:00 p.m. in the main theater of the Washington D.C. Temple Visitors' Center.

In addition to the Oaks speaking, newly baptized members of The Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints will be introduced and two of them will briefly speak. 

Washington D.C. Temple Visitors' Center
9900 Stoneybrook Drive
Kensington, Maryland

ABOUT THE GILLESPIES

The Gillespies have served in many callings in the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints throughout the world. Elder Gillespie has served as a stake president, stake president, stake patriarch, mission president, a member of the 2nd Quorum of the Seventy and a temple president. 

Elder Gillespie earned a Ph.D. in civil engineering and worked as an engineer, and director of the U.S. Transportation Safety Institute.

Sister Gillespie worked as a radiologic technologist and department manager. She has served in all of the Church auxiliary organizations and as an ordinance worker in the Manti Temple. She has been a Relief Society and Primary President, an early morning seminary teacher, and a full-time missionary.
234197360117781.name: "Why I Believe" Fireside featuring the Gillespies

On March 31 and April 1, 2014, Tibetan-Americans and friends of Tibet are invited to Washington, DC for the Sixth Annual Tibet Lobby Day.

Sign Up Deadline: Friday, March 21, 2014

SIGN UP TODAY: http://action.savetibet.org/p/salsa/web/questionnaire/public/?questionnaire_KEY=716&killorg=True 

The success of Tibet Lobby Day depends on the participation and efforts of Tibet supporters like you. It is your opportunity to communicate directly with your elected representatives and let them know that they have constituents who care deeply about Tibet.

The U.S. Congress has long been a bulwark of support for Tibet, from giving His Holiness the Dalai Lama his first parliamentary forum in 1987, to millions of dollars in Tibet support programs every year. But at the same time it is of vital importance that we continue to remind our Members of Congress of their longstanding commitment to Tibet. Faced with the well-funded lobbying might of the Chinese Embassy, it is critical that we speak out to let our elected representatives know of the breadth and depth of support for the cause of Tibet amongst their constituents and ensure that Tibet continues to remain on their legislative agendas.

This event is a collaboration of U.S.-based Tibet Support Groups, and Tibetan Associations in the United States. The International Campaign for Tibet (ICT) will provide a lobbying training session, help set up meetings for all participants with their Members of Congress.

For more information, please contact your local Tibet group or contact ICT advocacy team at lobbyday@savetibet.org or ICT at (202) 785-1515.
237173636406962.name: Tibet Lobby Day 2014 in Washington DC

237398473124850.description:
¡Ven! Participa,  Convive y Construye
Un espacio para la Paz


La Fundación Juvenil de América por la Democracia y el Desarrollo Multilateral (FUNJADEM), como  cada año lanza de manera oficial su convocatoria para aquellos Jóvenes emprendedores caracterizados por sus grandes actitudes diplomáticas y que poseen los mejores deseos de optimizar las condiciones de vida a nivel mundial. FUNJADEM, como institución sin fines de lucro está invitada y te invita junto con ella a participar en esta conferencia con la misión de representar la República Dominicana.

Esta convocatoria que hacemos de conocimiento público, está encaminada para aquellos estudiantes que desean participar y representar a la República Dominicana, en la conferencia más grande de Naciones Unidas, National Model United Nations” (NMUN •DC 2014), que se realiza en la capital de los Estados Unidos de Norte América, específicamente Washington, DC, del 31 de octubre al 2 de noviembre del año 2014.

NMUN, fue creada en 1946 por la National Collegiate Conference Association (NCCA), el Departamento de Información Pública de las Naciones Unidas y el gobierno de los Estados Unidos de América, es un ambiente académico internacional que simula el trabajo que realiza la (ONU), en sus diferentes órganos, agencias y programas, siendo un espacio rico en educación, cultura e innovación.

FUNJADEM: Es una organización privada sin fines de lucro, caracterizada por la Democracia y el Desarrollo Multilateral, la cual tiene por objetivos diseñar, elaborar y aplicar medidas estratégicas a través de proyectos que impulsen o proporcionen a los jóvenes de América y sus asociados, la oportunidad de poder desarrollar su liderazgo en condiciones de libertad, dignidad, e igualdad humana, sin importar categoría étnica, cultura, clase social, sexo, idioma, color y religión.

FUNJADEM, también es una Organización No Gubernamental, (ONG), asociada a las simulaciones de Naciones Unidas, siempre y cuando estas no tengan fines de lucro y mucho menos tengan actitudes de corrientes elitistas, caracterizadas por la (burocracia y la oligarquía). Estamos agradecidos por el apoyo de toda la familia de las Naciones Unidas, en particular el Departamento de Información Pública y la Misión de EE.UU.Ante la ONU.

Si tienes la capacidad de leer, escribir, hablar y entender en el idioma ingles entonces reúnes las cualidades básicas para poder participar en la conferencia (NMUN • DC 2014) que se celebra en colaboración con el Centro de Estudios Internacionales de Osgood.

La Ceremonia de apertura Normalmente se lleva a cabo en el Departamento de Estado o en otro lugar de prestigio de Washington, DC. La Conferencia incluye una simulación de crisis en el Consejo de Seguridad y sesiones de información del comité de destacados oradores de la comunidad diplomática de Washington, DC.

Los jóvenes seleccionados por parte de FUNJADEM, recibirán una ardua preparación académica, tendrán la oportunidad de discutir las problemáticas que atentan contra la integridad de la comunidad internacional, y por medio de la negociación multilateral, el diálogo y el debate, finalmente tendrán que llegar a un consenso y emitir una resolución tras días de debates.

El perfil de los y las aspirantes a ser seleccionados consiste en ser jóvenes con edad entre 18 a 28 años, estudiante de educación superior, cursos técnicos o de educación media, que actualmente estén cursando 4to de bachillerato y que tengan conocimiento del sistema de Naciones Unidas, teniendo que demostrar interés y conocimiento sobre las problemáticas mundiales y los Objetivos de Desarrollo del Milenio (ODM), Pero en especial tener capacidad de liderazgo y trabajo en equipo; así como, para desempeñar sus funciones con responsabilidad, puntualidad, pero sobre todo tener un amplio dominio del idioma inglés.

Nota; Cada joven que aplique al proceso tiene que tener en cuenta que es su responsabilidad cubrir los gastos consulares, boleto aéreo después de obtener su visado y otros gastos que dependan del proceso en general. La fundación como institución sin fines de lucro entregará cartas de solicitud de patrocinio o ayuda económica para que los jóvenes puedan cubrir los gastos del proceso. 

PROCESO DE SELECCIÓN

Cada joven que tenga la voluntad de participar y representar a la República Dominicana con FUNJADEM en (NMUN • DC 2014) tendrá que asistir por lo menos a una Reunión Informativa en las fechas que presentaremos a continuación, entregar todos los documentos que le sean solicitado luego de ser preseleccionado, asistir al proceso de entrevista y someterse a un largo proceso de evaluación durante varios meses. 


REUNIONES INFORMATIVAS

Domingo (25 de Mayo). Se Realizará en el Salon de Reuniones, del  Primer Nivel de la Plaza Malecón Center que está ubicado en la Av. George Washington casi esquina Av. Máximo Gómez. Justo frente al Mar Caribe. En Horario de 2:00 Pm hasta las 4:00 Pm de la Tarde.

Domingo (1 de Junio). Se Realizará en el Salón de Reuniones, del  Primer Nivel de la Plaza Malecón Center que está ubicado en la Av. George Washington casi esquina Av. Máximo Gómez. Justo frente al Mar Caribe. En Horario de 2:00 Pm hasta las 4:00 Pm de la Tarde.


ENTREVISTAS

Las Entrevistas serán asignadas en orden de procedencias según el día que el Aplicante asista a la reunión informativa y luego entregue la documentación que le sea solicitada.

La Recepción y/o Aplicaciones de solicitudes estarán abiertas hasta el domingo 8 de junio del año en curso y los preseleccionados, serán contactados para un proceso de entrevistas que se realizará luego de entregar su documentación.

REQUISITOS DE ADMISIÓN

Los interesados deben enviar a la siguiente dirección de correo electrónico funjadem@hotmail.com los primeros cuatro (4) requisitos de la siguiente documentación y además del envió al correo de FUNJADEM, se deberá entregar en físico con los demás documentos el día de su entrevista con el formato de Letras Times New Román 12, Margen 3 cm y a 1.5 interlineado a 2 dos espacios.

1. Currículum Vitae.
2. Una semblanza que explique de manera resumida su historia de vida académica, social, familiar y/o laborar.

3. Ensayo Número uno (1) En Inglés, (5,00 Palabras).

• Tema: porque usted quiere participar con FUNJADEM, en NMUN.NY-2014 y cuáles son las razones de manera detallada que lo Motiva a regresar a República Dominicana después de participar en dicha Conferencia Internacional en Estados Unidos.

4. Ensayo Número dos (2) En Inglés, (1,000 Palabras).

• Tema: Todo lo referente al sistema de las Naciones Unidas, ONU. (Su historia, como funciona, de que se encarga y cuál es su estructura a nivel mundial).

EN HOJA DE HILO Y ENCUADERNADO.

5. Una Foto de cuerpo completo.
6. Fotocopia del Pasaporte (Opcional por el Momento).
7. Fotocopia de la Visa. (En dado caso de no tener visa nosotros gestionamos su proceso de entrevista consular para que el consulado determine si usted califica para una visa B1-B2).
8. Fotocopia de su Cédula.
9. Documentación oficial que acredite los últimos estudios cursados o los que se encuentre cursando en la actualidad (curso técnico, educación media o superior).
10. Carta de Buena Conducta emitida por la Procuraduría General de la República Dominicana, (Reciente).

No se recibirán expedientes incompletos y el Aplicante tendrá que conseguir todas las documentaciones adicionales que les soliciten las autoridades competentes de FUNJADEM, luego de su preselección para completar su proceso de selección.


¡Ven! Participa, Convive y Construye
 Un Espacios para la Paz.

¡Podemos Lograrlo!

237941253045844.description:
Overgrow the Government, the premier hosts of the annual National 4/20 Rally in Washington D.C. in unity With Maryland NORML and The International Women's Cannabis Coalition, cordially invites you to join us and other pro-cannabis organizations at Lafayette Park, at the front door of the Whitehouse for this year’s 4/20 March, Concert and Rally.

These organizations believe that the people of this great country stand to benefit greatly from the end of marijuana prohibition. Medicinally, recreationally, agriculturally and industrially, marijuana reform is important both socially and economically to the communities and families of the United States. Our rally aims to bring all cannabis reform organizations, activists and advocates together in unity to discuss, promote, entertain and educate both consumers and non-consumers alike on the benefits of marijuana and to call to our president and other U.S. leaders and legislators, to end marijuana prohibition nationwide.

With speakers like: 

Chris Hirsch –Outreach Coordinator for Maryland NORML & Founder of The People For The Cannabis Culture 


Rebecca Forbes - North Carolina’s own Queen of Cannabis. East Coast Director of the American Cannabis Coalition,  on the board of directors of Overgrow The Government, Carolina Cannabis Coalition, CEONC, and advocate for the Cash Hyde Foundation.

Wayward Bill – Chairman of the United States Marijuana Party

Judy Pentz – is the Executive Director of Maryland NORML and an advanced MS patient, medicating herself with solely cannabis, is a state that does not give her the legal right to. She is directly responsible for the tremendous growth of Maryland NORML membership in the last year.

Barry Considine - Local patient, political writer and activist. 

Michael Rivercomb Hickman- from Plain City Ohio, is the Vice President of the Ohio chapter of NORML, The Central Ohio regional coordinator for the Ohio Rights Group and a drug policy reform columnist for the Columbus Free Press. His speech is entitled "Changing the Dialogue for Legalization from "if" to "how"
 
Candace Junkin – is the Founder of the International Women’s Cannabis Coalition. Former Asst. Executive Director of Moms for Marijuana International and Treasurer and Board Member of Overgrow
 
Richard Kennedy  - along with his St. Bernard, Bismarck, is The Founder of Canines for Cannabis,  Richard is a former economist for the CIA and member of LEAP. He is also on the Board of Directors of Va. NORML and an expert on Virginia Cannabis Law.


AND MANY MORE. 3 Bands, Our Official DJ.. DJ Chukelz! A cannabis fact Easter Egg Hunt and lots more fun stuff! 

Concerts throughout the day from fabulous local bands: Troll Tribe, The Shawn Owen Band and Dug & Pen!!!! 

Events like this take time, work and money to happen. Please consider donating your time and/or making a donation to this great cause. Your generous monetary donation will ensure the success of Overgrow’s 4/20 rally in Washington D.C. You will make a difference in ensuring that this event not only happens, but will continue for years to come; until our voices are heard and marijuana prohibition ends. To make a donation to this great cause go here: http://www.overgrowthegovt.net/apps/donations/ 

For more info contact Rebecca Forbes at cccdirector420@gmail.com or Candace Junkin at candace.iwcc@gmail.com

HOPE TO SEE YOU ALL THERE!!!!!!

Please keep in mind that Lafayette Park is Federal Property. and people have been arrested there in past years for cannabis.  Leave yours at home!
-------------------------------------------------
^^^^^^^^^^^^^MARCH FOR FREEDOM!!!^^^^^^^^^^^^^
>>>>>>>>>>>>> 10 AM SHARP!>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>

For those who would like to march on DC! Bring your signs and meet us on the Northwest lawn of the Washington Monument. We will march for freedom down 17th street to Lafayette park!! The street address of the Monument is 15th St NW, Washington, DC. Find the Overgrow Group on the north west side of it. (the 17th St. side.)

The closest metro the Washington Monument is The Smithsonian station. Use the Mall exit. 

See you there! 

+++++++++++++*Tips for Lafayette Park:++++++++++++

Parking around the park is terrible! There is free street parking on Saturday and Sunday, but it is VERY limited!!! We advise you take the metro in and walk the 1 block to the park 

The closest metro station is McPherson’s Square, which is on the Orange and Blue lines. Exit toward the White House. You will see the park in one block. 

Please bring your signs and your banners. You can not leave them on the lawn and walk away. So you don't bring anything you don't want to hold at all times.

You can NOT bring chairs. 

Bring you own Food. Water. Etc. 

Please keep in mind that there will be D.C. Park Police AND Secret Service around us at all times. Leave your canna-meds at home and please act responsibly.

239230856280639.description:
We are marching One Million Pibble March on Washington DC in an effort create safe and humane communities for humans and pets. To give millions of voiceless victims a voice and by doing so, end discrimination and abuse. 

Now, more than ever before, broken young people all over this country are committing sociopathic acts against innocent voiceless beings.  Time and time again, studies have shown that people who commit violent acts against animals will likely and most often times do, go onto commit violent acts against humanity.  The breed being victimized by this abuse more than any other breed on earth, are Pit Bull Terriers.  Dogs that are loyal, loving, gentle and smart being forced to fight till the death.  The average age of dog fighters are 13-21 years old.   Questions to consider; What happened to them?’  Why are they so broken?  How do we help?  To “ban” a breed is not a solution but rather an ineffective way to try and fix what is an obvious reflection of a broken society.

The epidemic that is happening in our own backyards can no longer be ignored.  Whether you like Pit Bull Terriers or dogs at all, as a member of society this is all of our problem. Through education and effective solutions we can fix this social pandemic and provide a safe society for future generations of humans and animals alike.  It is time legislators recognize that discrimination enshrined in law is wrong,  factually ineffective and will no longer be tolerated.
239230856280639.name: One million pibble march. <3

240585772732365.description:
The FREE HER rally and campaign is organizing women and others in support of ending mass incarceration to gather on the Washington Mall to:
1. Raise awareness of the increase in the rate of incarceration of women in the United States and the impact on our children and communities
2. Demand an end to voter disenfranchisement for people with felony convictions
3. Ask President Obama to commute the sentences of women and men in the federal system who have applied for commutation
Women coming together to speak from one voice will raise awareness of the devastating impact that overly harsh drug sentencing policies have had on women and their children and how mass incarceration and the war on drugs has directly impacted our communities. In ten years the incarceration rate for women in general has increased 400% and 800% for african american women.
We are organizing buses from organizations from cities and states throughout the country to come together and use our voices as one. After the June rally we will use our organized voices to continue to call, email and send postcards to encourage the President and raise awareness among everyday people of the need to end the war on drugs and mass incarceration of women throughout the United States.

For Information contact:
Families for Justice as Healing
Rally@justiceashealing.org
(617) 749-3129

http://justiceashealing.org/
240585772732365.name: FREE HER RALLY 6/21

241099969425177.description:
Hinckley Pottery, which has been a vibrant center for pottery-making in the Washington area for more than 40 years, will be holding its 23rd Annual Student Show at its studio in Adams Morgan on Sunday, May 4th, 2014.

More than twenty experienced students will display a year’s worth of artistry for sale to the public. The potters work in stoneware and porcelain and incorporate more than 30 different glazes available at the studio ranging from vibrant blues and greens to ochre and rust. The show will feature platters, bowls, mugs, vases, teapots, and other vessels, and all of the pottery is meant to be used and enjoyed. 

Visitors are invited to come and meet the potters, enjoy delicious food, and find one-of-a-kind, handmade gifts for housewarmings, Mother’s Day, graduations, weddings, and everyday use.

Please feel free to share the invitation with others.  

Thanks!
241099969425177.name: Hinckley Pottery Student Show

Dancekraft brings your Tuesdays to the next level! Join us for a NietZsky's birthday bash along with special guest DJ's! 

Doors: 7:30pm
NO COVER
21+

DJ Daryl Northrop is a breaks, house, and electro DJ based in the Virginia suburbs of DC. DJ Daryl Northrop spins across the greater DC region, from Jimmy Valentines to Backbar at the 9:30 Club, and on to Paradox in Baltimore. He is also co-founder of the EDM collective Dancekraft which hosts genre-bending, innovative parties at venues in the DC region.
https://soundcloud.com/dnorthrop 

DJ Phaydn - ALL things drum and bass. A 15 yr veteran of the DMV scene, Phaydn lives life at 175bpm and has the amen-break encoded in his DNA. 
https://www.facebook.com/djphaydn


NietZsky - Classically trained, professionally unemployed. 
https://www.facebook.com/NietZsky

Dopethrown - Straight out of Baltimore, MD. Dopethrown has been making his way through the ever expanding scenes in Baltimore and Washington DC. As a long time Hip Hop producer with numerous album production credits, he first took his talents outside of hip hop, into the world of electronic music. This lead to different journeys across the spectrum, from Deep House, to Trap, to Dubstep, and everything in-between. Dopethrown finally settled in the field of Future Bass music, an area where he could incorporate his Hip Hop roots, but still bring energy infused club bangers to the masses. Dopethrown has burst into the electronic dance community, playing shows from intimate outdoor festivals, to some of the best clubs in the DMV.
https://www.facebook.com/Dopethrown

Traxiom - Traxiom is a multi-genre DJ, music producer, writer, and vocalist. You can find Traxiom rocking clubs and parties across the region. Primarily DnB but known to rock a wide range of genres including breaks and electro.
https://www.facebook.com/Traxiom

247377045464303.description:
The 2014 Annual Meeting (and Reception) of the Illinois State Society of Washington, DC will be Wednesday, May 14. We will be voting on new Proposed Bylaws for the Society, electing our Board for the next fiscal year and enjoy a speech by Marc Mappen about the rise of gangsters in the prohibition era. (note-drinks will be served!) The evening will include a short business meeting, election of State Society Board Members for 2014-15, our featured speaker, and a buffet dinner reception. 

May 14, 2014 
ISS Annual Meeting, Reception, and Guest Speaker 
University Club of Washington, DC. 
1135 16th Street, NW 
Washington, DC 20036 
6:30 p.m. 
* * * 
Admission is free to ISS Members and $25 for non-members. 

Valet Parking Available for 40 cars. Closest Metro: Farragut North -- Blue LIne; McPherson North -- Red Line. 

Professor Marc Mappen, of the Rutgers History Department, author of "Prohibition Gangsters, The Rise and Fall of a Bad Generation" will be the speaker for the May 14 Annual Meeting/Reception. A master storyteller, Mappen will apply a generational perspective to the gangsters of the Prohibition era - men born in the quarter century span from 1880 to 1905 - who came to power with the Eighteenth Amendment.

 He will focus on the major gangsters, including Illinois' Al Capone. Today the names of these men - Al Capone, Lucky Luciano, Dutch Schultz, Legs Diamond, Nucky Johnson - are more familiar than ever, thanks to such cable TV programs as Boardwalk Empire.

 Making use of FBI and other government files, trial transcripts, and the latest scholarship, Mappen will provide a lively narrative of shootouts, car chases, courtroom clashes, wire-tapping, and rub-outs in the roaring 1920s, the Depression of the 1930s, and beyond. Mappen asserts that Prohibition changed organized crime in America.

 Please invite your friends to attend. The evening promises to be quite entertaining. Admission is free to ISS Members and $25 for non-members. 

ISS looks forward to seeing you at the Annual Meeting on May 14 at the University Club. Please go the the Illinois State Society website to respond to the Annual Meeting at http://www.IllinoisStateSociety.org/

 Notice: Dues are now being accepted for Membership for the 2015 fiscal year - June 1, 2014 to May 31, 2015. Join and then tell friends about ISS by going to the Illinois State Society web page above to become a member. All 2015 fiscal year Members may attend the annual meeting free of charge. Hold on tight for all the fun to come! 

- Stuart Piper, President of the Illinois State Society of Washington, DC.
247377045464303.location: The University Club Of Washington DC
247377045464303.name: Illinois State Society Annual Meeting and Dinner Reception with Professor Marc Mappen and the topic: "The Rise of Prohibition Gangsterism in America". (note- drinks will be served!)

249060908551682.description:
Kino MacGregor Workshop - March 29th & 30th 

Saturday, March 29th, 9:00am - 11:00am: Ashtanga Yoga Full Primary Series 

Kino will guide the full primary series with careful emphasis on the traditional vinyasa method and have fun along the journey.

Saturday, March 29th, 1:00 - 3:00pm: Fly like a Bird - All About Bakasana 

Take the time to master the core strength, stable shoulder girdle and steady mind needed to mater Bakasana position. Translated into English as the Crane Posture, Bakasana unlocks the key principles of strength for all other arm balances. Start off with the easiest version of Bakasana and challenge yourself by trying some of the hardest versions of Bakasana like Eka Pada Bakasana A. Jump back and jump into Bakasana and learn how to transition in and out of handstand from the posture. Don’t let Bakasana trick you into thinking it’s too easy--come and learn how to be strong enough to truly fly like a bird.

Sunday, March 30th, 8:00am - 10:00am: Mysore Style Ashtanga Yoga 

The traditional Ashtanga self-practice with adjustments from Kino

Sunday, March 30th, 12:00pm - 2:00pm: Strong Steady Grace 

Built on the first two postures of the Ashtanga Yoga Third Series, Visvamitrasana and Vashitasana, this class helps you find your true strength in plank and beyond. You will explore these two challenging arm balances from every possible angle, breaking down the anatomical foundation of the postures and investigating the spiritual benefits of their daily practice. You will build up to flowing through these postures in the traditional vinyasa method and then apply the key principles learned through these two postures to other difficult arm balances. These two postures are named after two of India’s most powerful sages and you will attune yourself to their spiritual strength and grace through the practice.

Full Weekend: $195
Individual Sessions: $55

All Kino Workshop sessions will be held at the Edmund Burke School, 41O1 Connecticut Avenue NW, Washington DC.

Please register at the studio or email elsie@woodleyparkyoga.com.

249060908551682.name: Kino MacGregor Washington, DC Workshop

259052657609795.description:
Led by Jeffrey Oliveira Platts and Melanie Curtin.

Small talk leads to small connections. DC can go beyond "What do you do?" and "How about this weather, huh?". Maybe you're tired of unfulfilling conversations in loud bars. Or perhaps you're craving more soulful connections with fun people. If so, then you've found your tribe. 

This month's theme is MAGIC and MYSTERY. 

TICKETS: https://dcargn-april11.eventbrite.com

What's Authentic Relating Games Night?

Authentic Relating Game Nights are inspired by the Game Nights held in San Francisco by Authentic World and dozens of cities around the world. Sometimes loud, sometimes intensely quiet, sometimes risky... always fun and revealing. 

Do you crave a space where you can talk about something OTHER than, "What do you do?" or "Where did you go to school?" Join a thriving DC community at Authentic Relating Games Night, a space where you can discover how much more FUN and rich it is to BE YOURSELF and actually connect with people. ALL are welcome. Bring a friend, bring your partner or come solo! NOTE: THESE ARE NOT SINGLES EVENTS. (Although phone numbers DO get exchanged occasionally...)

"This is ten times -- sorry, I mean ONE MILLION TIMES -- better than going to a bar." - Melanie C., 32 

"A unique and FUN way to connect with people on a deeper level. If you're curious about what a "games night" is (without any mention of Monopoly or Twister), do yourself a favor and experience this. Trust me." -- Adrial D., 29

WHAT KIND OF GAMES ARE THESE?
	•	Imagine a playground where you can practice the art of relating with others in a fun, social atmosphere. Game Nights create a safe place within which to play a little more outside our comfort zones. We discover more about ourselves than we might in our everyday lives, all within a lighthearted container that makes it easy to get real, take emotional risks, and grow on a personal level.
	•	The games are fun, highly interactive partner and group exercises that demonstrate and explore authentic relating. Get to know yourself better while also learning to see and appreciate more about everyone with whom you connect. The games are NOT board games like Chutes & Ladders and checkers.
	•	By authentic we mean that there is no cookie-cutter mold for how you should be or what relating should look like. Everyone is a universe unto themselves, with their own unique style, personality, and integrity. We hold that everyone is perfect and amazing exactly as they are (including their belief that they aren’t.) 
	•	Game Nights are a chance to have fun and party in a conscious way with great people, going beyond small talk and expected (and often boring) social norms.
	
WHAT CAN I EXPECT?
Laughter. Fun. Energy. More genuine connection. Excitement/anxiety (while learning the difference). Relief. Feeling alive and awake. Conversation beyond small talk. Play. Connection. New possibilities. New friends. Insights. Sparks. Challenges. Personal growth. Transformation. 

WHO COMES TO PLAY?
	•	Adventurous adults of all ages who want more fun, rich connections with people. Whether you're tall, short, old, young, in a relationship, single, or "it's complicated." ;) (Again, these are NOT singles/dating events.)
	•	You want the opportunity to experience an open-hearted space where people are given the space to cut through the superficial and act as truly themselves for an evening.
	•	You enjoy exciting, fun and very juicy social evenings with lots of laughs, plenty of insights, and sometimes sparks flying!
	•	You are looking for a real, authentic connection with new people and are prepared to take a risk to try something NEW.
		
DATE AND TIME
Friday, April 11, 7pm to 10pm

DOORS WILL CLOSE PROMPTLY 7:30pm (We really mean it!)
7:30pm - 10:00pm Authentic Relating Games
10:00pm to 10:30pm Enjoying the vibe!
Light refreshments will be provided
Tickets
$25 in advance (by Wednesday, April 9 at 5pm)
$35 at the door

Previous events have sold out. Only 20 spots available. Guaranteed spots are only for ticket holders. Walk-ins allowed only if space is available. 

ALL TICKETS ARE NON-REFUNDABLE. 

TICKETS: https://dcargn-april11.eventbrite.com

LOCATION
The Viva Wellness Center 
1900 Q Street NW (The Anchorage Building)
3rd Floor
Washington, DC 20036
(1 block from Dupont Circle Metro, on Q St across from Firehook Bakery)

Regulars: NOTE THE CHANGE IN LOCATION. Authentic DC events are no longer held at Past Tense Yoga Studio.

QUESTIONS?

Singer-songwriter Eli Conley from the Bay Area is coming to DC on his CD Release Tour. Wonderful songwriter Angie Head will headline the show, and a TBA local act will open. Please Note: B.Steady has had to pull out of this show due to unforeseen circumstances.

More Info Below 

All Ages, $10 Suggested Donation

Angie Head - http://angiehead.com/

Angie Head is a singer/songwriter/musician who has, in her time in Washington, DC, gained the attention and praise of those who admire inspiring talent. She is a skillful acoustic guitarist with a strong, sweet, soul-stirring voice. A graduate of the University of Michigan with a degree in Ethnomusicology (the study of music on the context of cultures), Angie frequently performed in the many coffeehouses and cultural events in the Ann Arbor area.The Washington Blade has described Angie’s performances as “sweet justice to songs by artists like Tracy Chapman and original pens.”

Eli Conley -  www.eliconley.com

Eli Conley is a Berkeley, California-based musician steeped in Americana music and the singer-songwriter tradition. He crafts modern day folk songs for misfits from the raw material of his life as a queer man with Virginia roots. "Oh what gorgeous, soulful music!" raved roots music innovator Laura Love, "Eli Conley's writing and singing are exquisite." Eli is on tour from the Bay Area to promote his debut studio album, At The Seams. He will be accompanied by Constance Sisk on electric cello and Joel Price on fiddle & mandolin.

263147827201573.description:
March and Rally in DC to Capitol Hill!

Join National People's Action, the National Domestic Workers Alliance and ROC United at 11:00am on Monday April 28th in Washington DC at the American History Museum on 14th Street and Constitution Avenue, NW. 

We'll be marching to the Capitol, with direct actions along the way, to show Congress that we're fed up with them favoring corporations over people. 

We're marching on this day because one of the most powerful lobbies in the country -- the National Restaurant Association -- will be in DC for their annual lobby day. The National Restaurant Association's anti-worker agenda has blocked minimum wage increases, paid sick day legislation, and kept the federal tipped minimum wage at $2.13 since 1991.

The U.S. Chamber of Commerce is another major player in the corporate fight to suppress wages. Of the 20 trade groups that wrote a March 21st letter to Congress claiming "raising the minimum wage will be detrimental to job creation and low-skilled workers trying to get started on the economic ladder," the Chamber spends by far the most on lobbying. It spent almost $75 million on lobbying in 2013, almost ten times the next biggest spender on that list. More info here: http://www.opensecrets.org/news/2014/04/the-political-money-against-the-min.html

The Chamber claims to represent the interests of 3 million businesses, but in 2012 it received more than half of its money from just 64 large donors. More info here: http://www.citizen.org/us-chamber-of-commerce-funders-dominated-by-large-corporations-report
263147827201573.location: Restaurant Opportunities Center of Washington DC (ROC-DC)
263147827201573.name: The Battle for the Capitol: Kick Corporate Cash out of Congress!

AMA Art Museum of the Americas to Showcase Reggae Posters in Washington D.C.

The AMA Art Museum of the Americas to curate a selection of 24 reggae posters from the International Reggae Poster Contest (IRPC) at the Organization of American States (OAS) headquarters in Washington D.C. This is the IRPC's seventh major “World-A-Reggae” exhibition. The exhibition will be co-hosted by the AMA and the Jamaica Mission at the Organization of American States (OAS) Marcus Garvey Hall.  The 24 beautiful posters come from  designers from around the world. The poster exhibition will run from May 19th through the 31st and admission is free. 

Opening Reception: 22th May, 2014, 6:00 pm at the OAS Headquarters; His Excellency Stephen Vasciannie, Ambassador of Jamaica to the U.S. and head of the Permanent Mission of Jamaica to the OAS, Professor Carolyn Cooper of the University of the West Indies, Michael Thompson and Maria Papaefstathou, founders of the contest, will speak at the opening.  

Where: Organization of American States (OAS). Marcus Garvey Hall:  200 17th St NW, Washington D.C. 

For further information and details of the exhibition, contact : 
Andrés Navia: anavia@oas.org Director, Art Museum of the Americas;  or 
Julia Hyatt: juliaehyatt@gmail.com, Minister/Alternate Representative, Permanent Mission of Jamaica to the OAS.

268383903339548.description:
Informed by comparative planetology and a survey of the major episodes in Earth history, this lecture will offer a taxonomy of planetary catastrophes meant to illuminate the unusual nature of the "Anthropocene", the current era of human-driven planetary scale changes, and reframe our current environmental and technological predicaments as part of a larger narrative of planetary evolution. This saga has now reached the pivotal moment when humans have become a dominant force of planetary change, and geological and human history are becoming irreversibly conjoined.
Is this a likely or even inevitable challenge facing other complex life in the universe? Possible implications for exoplanet characterization and SETI will be considered, as well as the choices our civilization faces in attempting to create a wisely managed Earth.

Biography: 
David Grinspoon is a Visiting Scholar in Astrobiology at the Library of Congress and Adjunct Professor of Astrophysical and Planetary Science at the University of Colorado. An internationally known Planetary Scientist funded by NASA to study the evolution of Earthlike planets elsewhere in the universe, Dr. Grinspoon serves as an advisor to NASA on space exploration strategy. He serves as Interdisciplinary Scientist on Venus Express, the European Space Agency's first mission to Venus. He has also lectured and published widely. His first book, Venus Revealed, (Perseus Books, 1998) was a Los Angeles Times Book Prize finalist. His latest book, Lonely Planets: The Natural History of Alien Life won the 2004 PEN Center USA Literary Award for Research Nonfiction. His popular writing has appeared in Slate, Scientific American, Natural History, The Sciences, Seed, Nature, Astronomy, the Boston Globe, LA Times and the New York Times. His technical papers have been published in Nature, Science, and numerous other journals. Dr. Grinspoon has been featured on numerous television (PBS's Life Beyond Earth; BBC's The Planets) and radio (NPR’s Science Fridays, Wisconsin Public Radio, BBC World Service) shows. He has given invited talks at international conferences throughout the U.S., Europe, and Australia.
The American Astronomical Society awarded him the 2006 Carl Sagan Medal for excellence in public communication of planetary science. Grinspoon holds degrees in Philosophy of Science and Planetary Science from Brown University and a doctorate in Planetary Sciences from the University of Arizona.

Saturday, May 10, 2014 at 8:00 p.m.

Tickets:  $20 general -- $15 students and seniors

To purchase tickets, contact The Greenberg Theatre. Box Office at 202-885-2587 or http://american.tix.com
Tickets are also available at the theater prior to the concert.

For more information visit: http://kistatucker.com/american.php

Kista Tucker Insights, a company from the Washington, DC Area, and Trajectory Dance Project, a company from Baltimore, MD are excited about sharing a concert at The Greenberg Theatre in Washington, DC.  Without this joint effort neither TDP nor KTI would be able to afford this production.  We could find an alternative space, a tiny theater space, or a sight specific space, but they do not support the type of work we want to present.  We need a sophisticated space with a good floor, more than adequate lighting, suitable seating, and professional production elements.  So, Alice Howes, of Trajectory Dance Project and Kista Tucker, of Kista Tucker Insights got together and decided to share this venue.

KTI is premiering a new work, "David's Fire." with music composed and performed by David O'Malley.  This piece was originally titled "Astri--or not," but through the rehearsal process things changed, and so did the name of the dance.  Additional works presented by KTI are "Obstacles," "The Archetypes," and "Maga," performed by Tucker, herself.

Movement Artists performing with KTI are Clare Davidson, Julie Hart, Tiffanie Horner, Eliza Talbott, Kista Tucker, and Jennie Wills.

TDP is performing "Ragtime Nocturne," "The Body Is Not An Apology," three sections of "Women of Shakespeare," and "Slight of Hand."

Movement Artists performing with TDP are Kelly Alt, Melinda Blomquist, Kiara Davis, Alice Howes, Frances James, Catherine Oh, Sarah Joy Stallsmith, and Alicia Williams.

The Holmes Brothers, with Sol Roots opening
Doors: 7:00 pm / Show: 8:30 pm
$20 in advance, $25 day of show
This event is 21 and over

Blend of blues, gospel, soul, R&B, rock 'n' roll, and country. 

The Holmes Brothers
“Timeless, deeply soulful and uplifting gospel-drenched blues, street corner doo-wop, ballads, R&B, country and funk.” –The New York Times

"Fervent, inspired and joyful blues, R&B, soul, roadhouse rock and gospel…beautiful harmonies, true magic." –NPR

“Great songs, whether we write them or not, bring great things,” says guitarist/pianist/vocalist/songwriter Wendell Holmes. “And we are all about striving to write, find and perform great songs.” The Holmes Brothers—Wendell, bassist/songwriter/vocalist Sherman Holmes and drummer/vocalist and brother-in-spirit Popsy Dixon—are true treasures of American roots music. For 35 years, The Holmes Brothers’ joyous and moving blend of blues, gospel, soul, R&B, rock ‘n’ roll and country has been captivating audiences around the world. Their spine-tingling three-part harmony singing, mixing Wendell’s gruff and gravelly vocals with Popsy’s soaring falsetto and Sherman’s rich baritone, brings the spirit of gospel-inflected deep soul music into every song they perform. Equally gripping is the rhythmic foundation laid down by Sherman’s bass playing and Popsy’s drumming, perfectly complementing Wendell’s blues-soaked guitar solos and church-inspired piano playing. The band expertly blends Saturday night’s roadhouse rock and blues with the gospel passion of Sunday morning’s church service. Rolling Stone says The Holmes Brothers play “impressive, fervent country soul.” Entertainment Weekly goes further, declaring “The Holmes Brothers are juke joint vets with a brazenly borderless view of American music...timeless and rapturous.”

The band’s new Alligator Records album, Brotherhood, was produced by Glenn Patscha (Ollabelle, Marc Cohn), Chris Bruce (Me'Shell NdegéOcello, Seal) and Hector Castillo (Brazilian Girls, David Bowie). It is another stellar chapter in The Holmes Brothers’ storied and still-evolving history. It’s also their most bluesy album to date, filled with roadhouse wisdom, late-night doo wop, proto rock ‘n’ roll punch, soulful R&B and closing with an amazing dose of Sunday morning spirit. Featuring fourteen songs—including eight new Holmes Brothers originals and six carefully-chosen covers—Brotherhood finds The Holmes Brothers at the absolute top of their game, creating timeless roots music. From the rocking Wendell original Stayed At The Party, to the sweet harmonies of Ted Hawkins' I Gave Up All I Had, to Sherman's soulful composition Passing Through, to the doo wop splendor of Popsy's vocals on the Stax classic My Kind Of Girl, to Wendell's gorgeous duet with his daughter Felicia on Loving You From Afar, to the final note of the band's most requested song—and a highlight of each and every live performance—the soul-stirring Amazing Grace, Brotherhood is a testament to the uplifting musical power that comes from the close-knit, fraternally telepathic relationship of The Holmes Brothers. “As much as I love all of our albums, this is among my favorites,” says Wendell. “We worked hard. We tried for a live, loose feel and we got it. Glenn, Chris and Hector captured The Holmes Brothers sound most distinctly.”

From winning multiple Blues Music Awards to sharing stages and recordings with Bob Dylan, Van Morrison, Bruce Springsteen, Joan Osborne, Willie Nelson, Lou Reed, Peter Gabriel, Merle Haggard, Al Green, Ben Harper, Lucinda Williams, Steve Earle, Levon Helm, Rosanne Cash, Odetta, Marc Cohn and The Jungle Brothers, The Holmes Brothers have seemingly done it all. USA Today says that band is “glorious...full of soul and surprises.” The New York Times declares The Holmes Brothers “deeply soulful, uplifting and timeless.”

Their journey started in Christchurch, Virginia, where Sherman and Wendell were raised by their schoolteacher parents, who nurtured the boys’ early interest in music. As youngsters they listened to traditional Baptist hymns, anthems and spirituals as well as blues music by Jimmy Reed, Junior Parker and B.B. King. According to Wendell, “It was a small town, and my brother and I were about the only ones who could play
anything. I guess you could say we were large musical fish in a small pond. So we played around in all the area churches on Sundays.” The night before, though, they would play blues, soul, country and rock at their cousin’s local club, Herman Wate’s Juke Joint. “When he couldn’t get any good groups to come from Norfolk or Richmond, he’d call us in,” Wendell recalls. “That’s how we honed our sound. We used to say we’d rock ‘em on Saturday and save ‘em on Sunday.”

Sherman studied composition and music theory at Virginia State University, but in 1959 he dropped out and headed to New York for a promising job with a singer named Jimmy Jones (of Handy Man fame). His younger brother Wendell joined him in New York after completing high school. The two brothers played in a few bands before forming The Sevilles in 1963. The group lasted only three years, but they often backed up touring artists like The Impressions, John Lee Hooker and Jerry Butler, gaining a wealth of experience. Sherman and Wendell met drummer Popsy Dixon, a fellow Virginian, at a New York gig in 1967. Dixon sat in with the brothers and sang two songs. “After that second song,” recalls Wendell, “Popsy was a brother.” They continued to play in a variety of Top 40 bar bands—Wendell even toured with Inez and Charlie Foxx (Mockingbird)—until 1979, when the three officially joined forces and formed The Holmes Brothers band.

In the early years, the band worked primarily at Dan Lynch’s, a New York club that featured weekly jam nights and performances by a wide variety of blues acts, most notably The Holmes Brothers. More importantly, the club served as a meeting ground for many members of New York’s blues community, including future members of Blues Traveler, Joan Osborne and producer/harmonicist Andy Breslau, who brought the group to Rounder Records.

Since their debut on Rounder in 1989, The Holmes Brothers have toured virtually non-stop. They’ve performed in 50 different countries, including dates across the United States, Canada, throughout Europe, and in Singapore, Japan, Russia, Turkey, South America, Africa, Australia and New Zealand. In addition to their four critically acclaimed Rounder albums, they recorded Jubilation for Peter Gabriel’s Real World label in 1992, becoming the first American group to record for the standout world music imprint. 1996 found The Holmes Brothers starring in the independent motion picture Lotto Land, for which they also recorded the soundtrack. Their albums all received massive praise. “Mind-blowing,” said the Boston Herald. “Rich and satisfying,” raved The Washington Post.

The Holmes Brothers joined Alligator Records in 2001, releasing the Joan Osborne-produced Speaking In Tongues to overwhelming popular and critical acclaim. They followed with 2004’s Simple Truths, 2007’s State Of Grace and 2010’s Feed My Soul (which debuted at #1 on the Billboard Blues Chart), each release earning the band more fans and more accolades. The success of their albums led to multiple appearances on national television, including visits to The Late Show With David Letterman and two trips to Late Night With Conan O’Brien, as well as a rousing performance on CBS Saturday Morning. Profiles and concerts on NPR have put them in front of millions of listeners. They have appeared on Weekend Edition, All Things Considered, A Prairie Home Companion and performed on NPR Music’s Tiny Desk Concert. They played their original song Opportunity To Cry with Willie Nelson for the Willie Nelson & Friends: Outlaws And Angels TV special. The Holmes Brothers have been featured in countless newspaper and magazine articles and continue to tear up the highway, touring across the country and around the world. Greg Kot of The Chicago Tribune said The Holmes Brothers are a “joyous, foot-stomping carnival...a gift to the world of music.”

All of The Holmes Brothers’ musical gifts are displayed in full force on Brotherhood. With their deeply soulful singing, uplifting harmonies and unsurpassed musicianship, The Holmes Brothers’ ability to deliver gospel fervor and raw blues intensity is as legendary as their ability to bring audiences to their feet. The band is eager to bring their new release to the stage. “We’re looking forward to exposing the new songs to our fans, and bringing new fans to our songs,” says Wendell. “If you stay ready, you don’t have to get ready, and The Holmes Brothers are always ready.”

Sol Roots 
"Sol is a fierce guitarist and soulful singer" - Jambase.
Sol's talent stretches from fiery rock to laid back jazz, and from funky innovative grooves to soulful ballads, drawing on a deep background in raw down-home blues.
Sol has performed on stage and in the studio with musical heavyweights Taj Mahal, Kenny Wayne Shepard, and with the international guitar hero Cool John Ferguson (nominated 2 years -Most Outstanding Guitarist-Living Blues), who he performed with steadily for years. With Cool John, Sol has opened for the great B.B. King, Derek Trucks Band, and other musical luminaries.
272749639568462.name: Sol Roots @ Gypsy Sally's - Washington, DC

273098076200887.description:
We invite you to attend the Washington, DC premiere of Tohoku Tomo　東北友. We are thrilled to host this screening at The Miracle Theater during the National Cherry Blossom Festival. 

Tickets are available for a suggested donation of $10.

About the Film:

The story of true friendship and commitment to Japan's recovery by the international community following the Great East Japan Earthquake.

On March 11, 2011, while the rest of the world watched, much of the northeastern coast of Japan was washed away by the massive tsuanmi, triggered by a 9.0 earthquake. The tragedy was devastating to Tohoku, Japan, and the world. People lost loved ones, their homes, and even their way of life, Now, three years later, while the world's attention has moved on, the people of Japan are still struggling to pull their communities back together.

In the months following the disaster, countless volunteers rallied from around the world and came to Japan's aid to help begin the long process of rebuilding. Whether by donating money, organizing events, or coming to volunteer, these individuals showed they truly care about Japan and about the people of Tohoku. They are, in Japanese, Tohoku Tomo.

This is their story. 

The film includes over a dozen interviews, footage from the impacted areas, and features J-Pop artist Maynard Plant from the band Monkey Majik; Stu Levy, producer of the film Pray for Japan; and host of Tokyofoodcast, Etsuko Nakamura.
273098076200887.name: Tohoku Tomo - Washington, DC Premiere

273208166193617.description:
Come out on Saturday, May 3 to demand the release of Raif Badawi and be part of a global movement standing up for fundamental human rights! 

*****

30-year-old Raif Badawi, a Saudi Arabian writer and activist, was sentenced last year to seven years in prison and 600 lashes. Badawi’s crimes? Founding a website, Liberal Saudi Network, dedicated to fostering open discussion of religion and politics; and calling on his country to respect freedom of religion, belief, and expression, and women’s rights.

According to the Saudi court, Badawi was guilty of ridiculing Islam. In the midst of his appeals process, Badawi could soon be charged with apostasy. The penalty for apostasy in Saudi Arabia is death.

To make matters worse, a Saudi court recently jailed Badawi’s lawyer, Waleed Sami Abu Al-Khair, for his human rights activism.

Badawi did nothing more than peacefully exercise his basic human rights, and seek to help others secure the liberty to do the same, yet he is now in very real danger. Having lost his freedom, many in Saudi Arabia now call for his death. 

In support of Badawi, Muslims for Progressive Values and the Center for Inquiry are organizing a protest at the Saudi Arabian Embassy on Saturday, May 3, at 3:00 p.m. The embassy is located at 601 New Hampshire Ave NW, Washington, D.C. 20037, near the Foggy Bottom stop on the Metro. 

The D.C. protest is part of several demonstrations set to take place May 3, organized under the banner of Stand for Raif Badawi on World Press Freedom Day. Other protest locations include Ottawa, Canada; Madrid, Spain; Bern, Switzerland;  Paris, France, and Tunis, Tunisia.

Attendees are encouraged to bring their own signs, though some signs will be provided.

More information:

www.mpvusa.org
www.centerforinquiry.net
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raif_Badawi
http://www.amnesty.org/en/library/info/MDE23/001/2014/en

275579172619591.description:
Order tickets via Eventbrite:
http://dctechafrique.eventbrite.com/?aff=efbevent


 

With the confluence of low-cost, high-speed internet and access to mobile telephony, the Africa region is increasingly producing companies that are active contributors to global technology innovation.  Whether its in the humanitarian and emergency response domain(Ushahidi) or commercial(iRoko Partners, Jumia, MPesa), or the entrance of leading companies such IBM, Microsoft, and Google who have set up offices on the continent, tech innovation has firmly become part of the African narrative.

Come join us for three days and three events, where you will experience what the continent and Diaspora innovators have to offer.

Lineup of Events:

April 26th - Hackathon for Revisionprep

Time: 10AM April 26th -9:59AM April 27th

Description: 

We want to encourage collaboration between students, artists, and software consultants, engineers, international development professional and anybody else interested in creating transformative education technology for Africa. Tiphub & Mansa Colabs aim to catalyze the innovation in Africa and the African diaspora by supporting developers and applications that address community needs, while demonstrating to local leaders and decision makers how mobile technologies can lead to the next generation of tech jobs and investment.

RevisionPrep, an African Diaspora youth lead venture, is developing a gamified online social learning tool that offers an alternative to traditional exam preparation in Ghanaian Junior High Schools for the national Basic Education Certificate Examination (BECE). Every ninth grade student in Junior High School seeking admission to public Senior High Schools in Ghana is required to take the BECE. Based on performance on the exam, students are placed into specific high schools in the country.

Hackathon Prompt:

Using a cross-disciplinary set of teams, attendees will assist RevisionPrep identify opportunities/challenges in market size, think through curriculum materials, user-experience and/or back-end data collection needs.

 

April 27th - Site launch for Africandevjobs.com

Time: 6:30pm-8pm

Description:

AfricanDevJobs.com connects organizations and people who are focused on Africa’s growth and development. Through employment opportunities and career advancement resources for professionals, the organization is committed to social and economic development in Africa.  The social enterprise provides a platform for recruitment, networking, and information in African development.

This launch event is open to African development professionals, employers, and enthusiasts. There will be a demo of the new online platform that is making African development career exploration easier and the founder will also be present to answer your questions.  

April 28th - Fireside Chat with Enyo Kumahor, Managing Director ThoughtWorks Africa

Time: 6:30pm-8pm

Description:

Betty Enyonam Kumahor is the Regional Managing Director of Pan-Africa for ThoughtWorks, a global IT consulting firm. Nominated as Best African Company of the Year 2013 by African Business Awards, ThoughtWorks has already made a marked impact on the continent with a diverse portfolio of clients including some of the largest, most innovative, and socially impactful organisations on the continent.

Enyo joined ThoughtWorks from Ernst & Young where she led the led Ernst & Young’s Service Delivery Technology function for their Global Advisory practice deploying technology solutions across the 140+ countries where Ernst & Young operates. Enyo also expanded their IT and Program Advisory Services practices for Ernst & Young in West Africa, building a multi-million dollar practice providing program advisory, IT audit, IT risk management, IT transformation and outsourcing advisory services to clients spanning multiple industries including telecommunications, financial services, as well as government and public sector.
275579172619591.location: Impact Hub DC, 419 7th St. NW, 2nd Floor, Washington , D.C., US
275579172619591.name: DC Tech Afrique

276054575892863.description:
On March 31 and April 1, 2014, Tibetan-Americans and friends of Tibet are invited to Washington, DC for the Sixth Annual Tibet Lobby Day.

The success of Tibet Lobby Day depends on the participation and efforts of Tibet supporters like you. It is your opportunity to communicate directly with your elected representatives and let them know that they have constituents who care deeply about Tibet.

The U.S. Congress has long been a bulwark of support for Tibet, from giving His Holiness the Dalai Lama his first parliamentary forum in 1987, to millions of dollars in Tibet support programs every year. But at the same time it is of vital importance that we continue to remind our Members of Congress of their longstanding commitment to Tibet. Faced with the well-funded lobbying might of the Chinese Embassy, it is critical that we speak out to let our elected representatives know of the breadth and depth of support for the cause of Tibet amongst their constituents and ensure that Tibet continues to remain on their legislative agendas.

This event is a collaboration of U.S.-based Tibet Support Groups, and Tibetan Associations in the United States. The International Campaign for Tibet (ICT) will provide a lobbying training session, help set up meetings for all participants with their Members of Congress.
276054575892863.name: Team Boston for 2014 Tibet Lobby Day at Washington DC

The next Global Leaders event in DC will take place on Thursday April 24th where I will host Dr. Najib Ghadbian, Special Representative of the Syrian Opposition Coalition to the United States. 

Dr. Ghadbian and I will focus on Syria’s horrifying civil war and discuss the potential destabilization of the Middle East, the Obama administration’s response to the conflict, and the prospect, if any, of a political solution.  

A Syrian pro-democracy activist and academic, he served on the Board of the Day After Project, a cooperative movement by members of the Syrian opposition to outline a plan to rebuild the country and end the Syrian conflict once Bashar al-Assad is ousted from power. He serves as a Board member of the Syrian Center for Political and Strategic Studies, and is a founding member of the Democratic Network in the Arab World. Dr. Ghadbian is a signatory to the Damascus Declaration (2005), and was a founding member of the Syrian National Council (SNC).

278702105624041.description:
http://rollingthunderrun.com/run27/ 

Sunday, May 25, 2014
Rolling Thunder will assemble at the Pentagon Parking Lots – 7:00 a.m. and start departing at Noon.

Rolling Thunder’s mission is to educate, facilitate, and never forget by means of a demonstration for service members that were abandoned after the Vietnam War. Rolling Thunder has also evolved into a display of patriotism and respect for all who defend our country.

FIRST AMENDMENT DEMONSTRATION RUN

The Rolling Thunder First Amendment Demonstration Run is an annual ride and gathering that first started in 1988. Riders from around the nation, and even around the world rally in the Pentagon parking lots and begin the run through the streets of Washington, D.C. Afterward, it is an opportunity to meet old and new friends, pay respect at the memorials and participate in the Memorial Day events.

LEGISLATION

Our mission also includes legislative efforts. Rolling Thunder strives to affect national policy in a way that will assist POW/MIA’s. We wrote, got introduced and passed, the Missing Service Personnel Act of 1993.
278702105624041.name: Rolling Thunder XXVII- Washington DC

282254218608226.description:
Dear friends of Nigeria,
The Voices of Women and Children in Africa and Diaspora in collaboration with the Howard University African Studies Department's Graduate Students Association, Amnesty International, (USA), , Institute for Policy Studies, African Faith and Justice Network , Washington DC are calling on all nations to protest and demand for the release of the Nigerian girls abducted by the Boko Haram terrorist group in Nigeria.
This is going to be a peaceful protest at Dupont Circle, Washington, DC on May 9th at 12 noon.
We stand in solidarity with the nation and with the families of the abducted Nigerian girls.
The objective of this demonstration is to show support and solidarity to the parents of the Nigerian girls abducted last month by the Nigerian terrorist group Boko Haram.
Our demands:
We denounce the Boko Haram activities, especially terrorizing our children. We demand that the Nigerian government see to the end of terror as well as asking the global community to intervene to see that the girls are returned to their rightful families immediately unharmed.
That the Nigerian government review its security policies and increase its presence to give more protection to school children
That president Jonathan’s administration investigates why the military and police at the school did not protect the children when the terrorists came to the school
And that the principal of the school where the children were abducted be  interrogated for child negligence for allowing strangers to pick children up without proper identifications.
That an In-depth investigation should be carried out within the ranks and files of the Nigerian military to see if there are some elements in the military that 
That an In-depth investigation should be carried out within the ranks and files of the Nigerian military to see if there are some elements in the military that are sympathetic to BM terrorist group. We demand that security to be beefed up in Boko Haram strongholds.

Signed
Eucharia Mbachu
President and CEO, Voices of Women and Children in Africa and Diaspora
WWW.vowac.org
Barthseba Bryant   
President:  African Studies Graduate Association  Howard University 
Fr. Aniedi, Okure (AFJN)
Emira Woods(IPS)
Adotei Akwei (AIUSA
Lydia  Kawere Levy and Eucharia Madueke Snd  PhD Candidates, African Study Department, Howard University

283144145181755.description:
THE MOST IMPORTANT PANEL FOR ANYONE WHO WANTS TO KNOW OR GET INTO CREATING COMICS

Saturday, April 19, 2014
10:45 AM to 11:45 AM
Room 209B

Creating your product is only half the work it takes to succeed in the comics industry. What about the other half that we don’t see as clearly after the product is released to the world? This important panel will explore what it is like to be on the other side of the table, as a creator. We will discuss what it takes to exhibit at conventions, promote yourself, gain a loyal audience, and hopefully survive the life as comic book creator in today’s wild west industry – from the POV of professionals already behind the table. Moderated by filmmaker/comic writer Joe Carabeo.

Awesome Con Panelists: Joe Carabeo, Carolyn and Joe Show, Steve Conley, Matt Dembicki, Arsia Rozegar
283144145181755.name: The Other Side of the Table: Lessons from Creators (Washington DC Edition)

288158374642044.description:
Rolling Thunder is an annual motorcycle rally that is held in Washington, DC during the Memorial Day weekend to call for the government's recognition and protection of Prisoners of War (POWs) and those Missing in Action (MIAs). The tribute to American war heroes started out in 1988 with 2,500 participants. Now approximately 900,000 participants and spectators are involved with this annual demonstration in Washington, DC.

See Photos of Rolling Thunder 

2014 Rolling Thunder Memorial Day Schedule
Friday, May 23, 2014
 Candlelight Vigil - 9:00 p.m.
Vietnam Veterans Memorial, Washington, DC

 Saturday, May 24, 2014
 Wreathlaying Ceremony – 11:00 a.m.
U.S. Navy Memorial
 701 Pennsylvania Ave. NW, Washington, DC (On the Plaza)

 Saluting Our Troops - Schedule to Be Announced
 Henry Bacon Dr. and Constitution Ave.
 The Stage is just north of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial, Washington, DC

 Sunday, May 25, 2014
 Rolling Thunder will assemble at the Pentagon Parking Lot - 7:00 a.m. - Noon.
 Departure To Washington, DC - Noon
See a Map of the Route
 Speaker Program - 1:30 p.m.
 Musical Tribute - 3:00 p.m.
 The Stage is located between the Reflecting Pool and the Korean War Memorial 
Tips for Attending Rolling Thunder
•The best viewing spots are along the Arlington Memorial Bridge and Constitution Avenue.
  
•Streets will be closed along the route from 10:30 a.m. to 4 p.m. Parking is limited. Public transportation is suggested. See a guide to using Metro. Stations nearby include Smithsonian, Metro Center, Judiciary Square, Federal Triangle and L'Enfant Plaza.
  
•Bring food and water or expect to wait in line.
  
•Dress appropriately and wear comfortable shoes.
  
•Take some time to pay tribute to America's war heroes by visiting the monuments and memorials on the National Mall.
  
•Bring your patriotic spirit and enjoy the day!

Rolling Thunder History
Rolling Thunder began as a demonstration following the era of the Vietnam War, which was a difficult time in America's history. Similar to today's political climate, our nation was divided over issues of peace and war. However, many of America's military were killed or missing in action and their remains were not being brought home to be respectfully buried and honored. In 1988, veterans of the Vietnam War rallied together their families, fellow veterans, and veterans' advocates to organize a demonstration at the Capitol Building in Washington, DC during the Memorial Day weekend. They announced their arrival with the roar of their Harley-Davidsons, a sound not unlike the 1965 bombing campaign against North Vietnam named Operation Rolling Thunder. Approximately 2500 motorcycles participated in this rally, demanding that the U.S. government account for all POW/MIA's. The group became known as Rolling Thunder and each year since has held an annual "Ride for Freedom" to the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Wall. 
Rolling Thunder Today
Rolling Thunder was incorporated as a class 501 C-4 non-profit organization and today has more than 100 chapters throughout the United States, Canada, Australia and Europe. The group is actively involved year-round in promoting legislation to increase veteran benefits and resolve the POW/MIA issue from all wars. They also provide financial support, food, clothing and other essentials to veterans, veterans' families, veterans groups, and women's' crisis centers.

 For more information about Rolling Thunder, visit their website at http://www.rollingthunderrun.com

288158374642044.name: 2014 Rolling Thunder Washington DC

Vegan Pro and Fit Fathers have partnered with Neal Barnard, M.D., PCRM and the Preventive Nutrition Series which starts March 31st in Friendship Heights! Washington, Maryland and Virginia residents who struggle with type 2 diabetes can attend a free workshop on Monday to learn how to avoid complications from the disease and reduce or eliminate the need for medications.

WHO: Diabetes researcher Neal D. Barnard, M.D., is president of the nonprofit Physicians Committee and an adjunct professor of medicine at the George Washington University School of Medicine and Health Sciences.

WHAT: Dr. Barnard’s free seminar highlights the best foods to prevent and treat type 2 diabetes. People who have or are at risk for type 2 diabetes will benefit from the seminar. Family members, health care providers, and friends are welcome and encouraged to join.

WHERE: Physicians Committee, 5100 Wisconsin Ave., N.W., Ste. 400, Washington, DC 20016. The Physicians Committee is located a few blocks from the Friendship Heights Metro station.

CONTACT: Simply select "going" to reserve a spot. Class participants will receive meal plans, grocery shopping lists, and nutrition resources for diabetes management.

WHY?: Close to 10 percent of Washington residents struggle with type 2 diabetes. If diabetes means endless medications, doctor visits, and unstable blood sugars, it’s time to turn it around. Dr. Barnard will showcase the best foods to help you lose weight, stabilize blood sugar, improve cholesterol, and reduce the need for daily pills and insulin shots.

View Dr. Barnard’s published studies and watch sample diabetes lectures at NealBarnard.org.

Follow Dr. Barnard on Twitter: @DrNealBarnard
Follow Fit Fathers on Twitter: @FitFathers

John Lindsay-Poland of the Fellowship of Reconciliation discusses what this means for the annual $25 billion in global U.S. military and police aid. Once again, we experience how the mobility of artists and performing arts are subject to administrative decisions beyond our control and understanding. We warmly thank the Kennedy Center for their constant and patient collaboration and investment to make the presentation of "AP15" possible.

    Sunday 6th April 2014, 20:00
    Kennedy Center
    2700 F St., NW - Washington, D.C. 20566

303194169834979.description:
WHAT IS IN HER WORDS ABOUT?

In Her Words takes us as far back as the 1920′s,  a time when crimes like lynching were legal and the 1940′s and 50′s of McCarthyism dictated that you could be accused of treason for any arbitrary thing. Now, imagine creating– amidst that environment of oppression– art that transcended race, bled through inequality and uplifted a nation.

In Her Words is a 50 minute theatrical musical that explores the intersection of race, gender and social activism through the lives of six legendary African-American creatives. In Her Words educates the audience while engaging them with emotional theater and musical moments that are drawn directly from the lives of the women portrayed. During the 2014 season, the women explored are:

    Zora Neale Hurston
    Lena Horne
    Nina Simone
    Katherine Dunham
    Billie Holiday
    Lucille Clifton
FOR MORE INFO, VISIT HTTP://WWW.INHERWORDSTOUR.COM

FREE SHOW
303194169834979.name: Liberated Muse Arts Group Presents IN HER WORDS in WASHINGTON, D.C.

Problem: 2011 UNAIDS reports, number of people living with HIV/AIDS are 34.2 million and 8 million PLWHA received ARV, 330 000 children who acquired HIV infection, 2.5 million people acquired HIV infected, 1.7 million died of AIDS related illne
ss 

BCARE USA INC. is exempt from federal income tax under section 501(c)(3) of the Code. Thus, BACRE is recognized as a public charity by the IRS.) and its partners. 

Origin: The idea of connecting the biggest International AIDS Conferences came to existence from AIDS 2006 Toronto, when B'Care for the first time formulated 'AIDS RIDE 2008', a complete bicycle ride that connected AIDS 2006 & AIDS 2008, on 52 days including 8 resting days! 

The aims and objectives of AIDS Ride 2014 are as follows: 
1) To raise awareness about HIV/AIDS, 2) To counter stigma and discrimination, thereby promoting and protecting human rights, and more specifically to embody in our actions the theme of the 20th International AIDS Conference (AIDS 2014), 3) To bridge the geographical space between the 19th International AIDS Conference (Washington DC, United States) and the 20th International AIDS Conference (Melbourne, Australia) and 4) Fundraising 

NOTE: BCARE's 'AIDS Ride' is an incredible journey of People living with HIV/AIDS and affected from one International AIDS Conference to the another International AIDS Conference or it's a geographic connection between the two biggest International AIDS Conferences, so please be noted that 'AIDS Ride' can also use other means of transport like hot air balloon to cross the rivers, planes for an ocean, including our usual plan of 'bicycle ride' carried on the grounds! We may use bicycle depending on the geographic connections we make! 

Attention Everyone: Our logo use of Australian flag is temporary until we build a logo. Any volunteer is welcome to design a logo for AIDS RIDE 2014, based up on the flag or National Animal etc
