357711417703449.description:
UrbanFUTURE's primary goal is to close the achievement gap in St. Louis. In order to do this, we strive to restore the connection between families, the school, and the community. In a city where the graduation rate has dropped below 50%, we find ourselves up against an enormous challenge. And yet we are constantly encouraged by the incredible tenacity of our UrbanFUTURE students at Fanning Middle School and Busch Middle School who are working hard both during and after the school day to improve their grades and become successful young adults.

Last year, 15 dedicated students from UrbanFUTURE earned their way to Washington, D.C. by participating in a rigorous research course and fundraiser. After such a successful trip, many students are eager to take on the challenge and make their way to our Nation's Capital. For most of our students, this will be their first time outside of the state.

In order to participate, each student is required to select a monument or landmark of interest in Washington, D.C. and spend the semester researching its history and significance. Last year our students were thrilled to visit the places they had learned so much about. From walking the halls of the Library of Congress to watching the historic changing of the guard at Arlington Cemetery, our students covered more ground in the three days than most had walked all year.

We are expecting over 30 students from Fanning and Busch to join this year's adventure to Washington, D.C. Follow along as students work their way toward this year's trip. Thanks to everyone who helps to make the Washington, D.C. trip possible for our students!
357711417703449.name: Support UrbanFUTURE going to Washington, D.C.

398774586930041.description:
Join National Domestic Workers Alliance National People's Action National Day Labor Organizing Network and friends for a creative action on Monday, April 28, 2014 at 9:00am in front of the White House to express our dismay at President Obama’s deportation policy and urge him to act quickly to issue administrative relief that will halt deportations and address the priorities of women, children, and families. We are calling on the President to use his authority to expand relief for immigrant families and give them the breathing room needed to fully participate and push forward the immigration reform debate.

In 11 million households across the U.S., children are missing their fathers, women are left with the difficult task of raising families without their partners, and the deep connections between members in mixed status families and communities are severed. These numbers continue to grow as the current deportation crisis tears apart 1,100 more families each day.

More than ever the time is NOW for the President to stop deportations and grant relief without delay. Together, we say #Not1More. 

****
¡Únete a la Alianza Nacional de Trabajadoras del Hogar, Acción Nacional del Pueblo, La Red Nacional de Jornaleros y amigos para una acción creativa en lunes, 28 de abril 2014 a las 9:00 am frente a la Casa Blanca para expresar nuestra consternación por la política de deportaciones del presidente Obama, e instarlo a actuar con rapidez para detener las deportaciones y abordar las prioridades de las mujeres, los niños y las familias. 

En 11 millones de hogares a través de los EE.UU., los niños viven con el temor que se van a llevar los padres, las madres y los padres se convierten en padres solteros de un dia para otro y se quedan con la tarea dificil de criar a sus familias sin sus parejas, y las conexiones profundas entre comunidades y miembros de familias de estatus mixto están siendo cortadas. Estos números siguen creciendo, en la crisis actual de las deportaciónes 1100 más familias estan siendo separados cada día.

Queremos que el President ponga un alto a las deportaciones ahora.  Juntos decimos #niunamas

Carl Cox | Nic Fanciulli | Saeed Younan

Saturday April 19, 2014
Doors  9PM | No dress code | Ages 18+
Bottle Service: Tables@echostage.com | 202.503.2331

Echostage • 2135 Queens Chapel Road NE • Washington, DC

OH YES OH YES!  ;-) The legendary Carl Cox is finally back in the nation’s capital! A professional DJ since his early teens. A musical ambassador and a veteran of acid house and a champion of techno – you name it, Carl’s been there and done it, never losing sight of his passions – playing music, breaking tunes and celebrating life.

Nic Fanciulli is a DJ, producer and label owner who has remained one of the UK’s finest exports in electronic music throughout the last decade. One of the last DJs to break through to international acclaim on the strength of his DJ’ing alone, Nic has since gone on to establish his own imprint, Saved Records, a label that remains proudly at the forefront of electronic music today.  But it is his genuine and unreserved love for the scene and bringing through new talent that has given Nic the longevity to remain at the top for so long.

Saeed Younan: A world class globe-trotting DJ, a recording artist, a sought-after remix producer, and head of his own record label. His performances are renowned for his technical abilities and precision. He effortlessly weaves and morphs tracks together into a seamless blend of house, techhouse, and percussive grooves, enhancing his music into a warm and sexy vibe. All the while building momentum by allowing the music to ebb and swell.

Glow Washington DC Presents:
NERVO | R3HAB

Saturday April 5, 2014

Doors 9 PM | No dress code | Ages 18+
Bottle Service: Tables@echostage.com | 202.503.2331

Echostage • 2135 Queens Chapel Road NE • Washington, DC
TICKETS GO ON SALE 2.25.14  AT NOON EST!!!!


From songwriters to artists and super-fans to superstars, electronic dance music’s first sisters – Mim and Liv Nervo of NERVO – have staged a miraculous climb onto the international stage, straight from the pit in front of it.

These multi talented DJ dynamos are the all-time top-ranking female DJs in the world, voted by their legions of fans to No. 16 on DJ Magazine’s influential 2013 “Top 100 DJs” poll. In-demand and beloved across the globe, their nonstop schedule takes them from the shimmering beaches of Ibiza, to their studio in their home-away-from-hometown of London, to the towering Main Stage of Electric Daisy Carnival in Las Vegas. This summer NERVO released “Not Taking This No More” (#1 on the Beatport Electro House chart). Their new single titled “Revolution”, a collaboration with R3hab and Ummet Ozcan, was released on Nov 11th via Spinnin Records and has spent 3 weeks at #1 on Beatport.

            A small number of DJ-producers can claim to touch the success that R3hab – real name Fadil El Ghoul – has earned over the course of his young career; in fact, the youngster’s rapid rise through the ranks of the electronic music world has been almost unsurpassed. If few DJs can say their own sound verges on a standalone and established genre; even fewer can do it in such a short space of time. R3hab’s brand of ‘Chainsaw Madness’ has created such a stir in the scene that time-honored acts are constantly in line to show their support – Tiesto, Afrojack and Calvin Harris (to name but a few) are all keen followers of the Dutchman’s signature noise. With three glow appearances under his belt, the district has long awaited his return. Needless to say, DC needs R3HAB!

435165259963079.description:
Sri Dharma Mittra is coming to Washington, DC for a full day of classes on April 6th at the Washington Convention Center!

Sunday April 6th
Washington Convention Center
Room 146 A/B/C

Learn more about Sri Dharma Mittra at http://dharmayogacenter.com/dharma/dharma.php

Schedule:
Community Mantra and Chanting: Kirtan with Hannah Allerdice 9:00-9:45am
By donation - all proceeds to the DC scholarship fund for the Dharma Yoga Center 
Come join us for an hour of singing about love and to love, in celebration of Dharma Mittra's teachings and his visit to the nation's capital. Kirtan is very old form of yoga that can remove negative emotions and brighten our hearts and minds. Feel free to bring musical instruments, family and children and friends.

Master Class by Dharma Mittra 10:00am- 12:00pm
$40 regular, $30 and $25 sliding scale options
Dharma Mittra helps guide each individual to quiet the turbulent mind for peace, contentment, and realization of the divinity within you. Be ready for an amazingly graceful yet extremely challenging practice steeped in 50 years of Dharma’s experience of the classical traditions. This class is for intermediate and advanced students and teachers. Dharma Yoga Registered Teachers, apprentice teachers and students, as well as teachers and students of all backgrounds from around the world, commonly take this class. Dharma Mittra has taught over 300 advanced asana variations, and offers lessons in many of these unique and now popular poses of today. You will be guided through a purifying relaxation at the end of the class, and begin cultivating the mind with invaluable and profound sacred teachings on the ethical rules, nature of being, yogic diet, ancient varied breathing practices and sound techniques. For regular practioners and yoga teachers. Caution: do not miss out.
 
Healing Relaxation and Meditation: Yoga Nidra with Dharma Mittra 12:00pm-1:00pm
$30 regular, $20 and $15 sliding scale options
Taught and developed by Sri Dharma Mittra, this guided restorative session helps you break free from the stress of the noisy and restless world that maintains its presence in our bodies and minds at all times. This practice will allow you to take the time to let all the cells of your physical body, joints and organs de-stress and begin to find balance. This result occurs on an unconscious level as your bodily systems become healthy, balanced and refreshed. You will then be ready to sit quietly for the final minutes in the practice of contemplative meditation, to bring your awareness even further within and guide you toward the Real Self deep in your heart. From this place, it will be easy for you to acknowledge, see and feel the unity in the diversity, the sameness of all. You will slowly realize “all is within” and “we are all one” as Dharma Mittra often says. 

All Levels Practice: Maha Sadhana with Dharma Mittra 3:00pm-6:00pm 
$40 regular, $30 and $25 sliding scale options
All are welcome to this physically and mentally challenging invaluable practice, which includes spiritual purification discourses conveying the ancient teaching into our modern lives. ”Each Posture is designed to bring a special state of conscious,” says Dharma, a backbend and inversion expert. You will be shown how to establish proper placement, alignment and the spiritual intention of each pose. He will ignite one-pointedness of mind and steady determination that will have you doing poses you never thought you could. In addition to the discourse and an in-depth, long and challenging asana (yoga posture) practice, the class features a healing deep relaxation and a reflective meditation practice. Included is a joyous "Devotional Dharma Asana Satsang Jam," where students can listen and join in lively music and offer their demonstrations of poses if they wish. Personal attention and helpful hints are given throughout the session as well as direction toward the real true goal of Yoga.

439751149503602.description:
Looking for a way to have fun and to fight cancer? 

The second annual Nike Women's Half Marathon, a race to benefit The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society, will take place along the historic streets of Washington, D.C. on Sunday, April 27, 2014. The organizers are looking to NCAWPA to provide another great group of enthusiastic volunteers. They loved us last year and want us back!
--------------------------------------------------------------
HOW DO I SIGN UP? [UPDATED 4/17/14]

Send your
1. Name
2. Email Address
3. Shirt size
to sharon.hong@ncawpa.org

The online system has capped our job site so the organizer needs to (manually) add new volunteers to the group on the back end (you'll be sent a waiver once she gets your email address).

WE NEED 12 MORE PEOPLE TO MAKE 40 VOLUNTEERS!!!

--------------------------------------------------------------

About the event
The Nike Women's Marathon began in 2004 in San Francisco, to commemorate the 20th anniversary of Joan Benoit Samuelson's historic victory in the first women's marathon in the Olympics. This year, the Nike Women's Half Marathon has again sold out, with the race having created a platform for The Leukemia & Lymphoma Society to raise over $134 million dollars through its Team In Training program's partnership with the Nike Women's Marathon. The Nike Women's Marathon race series provides a premium event experience that annually celebrates the strength, determination, and accomplishments of women worldwide.


WHAT CAPITAL CITY DRAGONS NEED: 40 volunteers
DATE: Sunday, April 27, 2014
VOLUNTEER SHIFT STARTS: 5:00 am (because the race starts at 7:00 am)
VOLUNTEER SHIFT ENDS: 8:00am

DUTIES: Get ready to encourage and cheer on runners as you help organize and manage the corrals as the official Pace Tape Holders at the Start Line. You'll be assisting in maintaining pace groups before they head out on their run.

More concrete details will come as we get updates from the organizers.


WHY VOLUNTEER?
Straight from the NCAWPA website: "Community service is the main focus of NCAWPA." Although most of our community service activities relate to water/boating, it doesn't always have to be about paddling all the time (gasp!) and the Nike Women's Half Marathon in DC needs our help.

Keep in mind that this event supports women's participation in sports, just as NCAWPA supports women's participation in paddling sports. (FYI, males can run in the event but the focus is on getting more women active and fit).


NEED MORE REASONS? OK then...
The event organizers are willing to again donate to the Capital City Dragons Youth Team fund if we can produce 40 volunteers!

You'll get a free official race volunteer t-shirt commemorating the second annual Nike Women's Half Marathon in DC.

- You do NOT need to be a NCAWPA member to volunteer but if you are bringing family or friends and they plan to volunteer with you, sign them up above.
- I do not have coordinator access to anything submitted into the system this year (their staff organizes the Start/Finish Line volunteers) so ensure you sign up early (to reserve your t-shirt size) and accurately!

And if you can't make it to volunteering this year, feel free to forward this email and send someone in your place!


Thanks in advance for your support,
Sharon Hong, MSW, LGSW
NCAWPA Youth Program Coordinator
Questions: youth@ncawpa.org

--------------INFO/RESOURCES--------------[ADDED 4/17/14]
Nike FAQs: http://www.nike.com/us/en_us/c/running/run-nike-women/we-run-dc/faqs

WHERE DO I PARK FOR RACE DAY?
There will be no designated race day parking available. Participants are advised to use UBER car services or the metro to get to the start line. Please note that the start and finish are in the same location, located at 9TH St NW & Pennsylvania Ave NW Washington, DC 20004. There are several metro stations within walking distance to the start/finish line. Metro lines will open early on race morning @ 5AM to accommodate race participants and spectators. Please visit www.wmata.com to plan your trip.
 
WHAT TYPE OF POST-RACE RUNNER TRANSPORTATION IS OFFERED?
Participants are advised to use the metro when departing the finish location. Please note that the start and finish are in the same location. There are several metro stations within walking distance to the start/finish line. You can visit www.wmata.com to plan in advance for post-race transportation.

COURSE MAP (Pay attention to this so you are not boxed in/blocked off after the race starts/when you need to leave): http://www.nike.com/content/dam/one-nike/en_us/Running/DC14/DC14_COURSE_MAP.pdf

Alliance Française de Washington and Malmaison are thrilled to invite you this last Dj's set by METTABBANA, part of the Francophonie Month in the nation's capital !

10pm: Opening Act by B. B. Tschack
 
B.B.Tschack had his musical eureka moment in the mid-80ies when he discovered Kraftwerk in his local small-town record store in Germany. Moving from Berlin to Washington, DC in 2008, he has experimented with infusing global sounds into his DJ sets, adding a quirk to the four to the floor. In the last years, BBT played at festivals like Burning Man, Figment and the PEX Summer Festival in the US and regularly spins at events hosted by Meso Creso in DC.
 
http://soundcloud.com/b-b-tschack


Midnight: Dj Set by METTABBANA

"Mettabbana’s musical journey began with collecting and listening to international music 8-tracks, cassettes and haphazard vinyl as a teenager in his native Kosovo. Today, his sets (including own tracks and remixes) usually consist of global organic bass music, melding raw analog and urban electronic music from Africa, Latin America, the Middle East, the Caribbean, his native Balkans and beyond. He has co-founded a number of monthly and bimonthly global music events in DC such as Analog Soul Club, Tropic of Bass and Meso Creso’s 1001 beats."

458355347587097.description:
HUFFINGTON POST ANNOUNCES "ONE MILLION PIBBLE MARCH ON WASHINGTON"-May 16th, 2013
http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/05/16/one-million-pibble-march_n_3280839.html?1368716232

HUFFINGTON POST-August 21st, 2013
"BARACK OBAMA COMES OUT AGAINST BSL AND JOINS THE FIGHT FOR PIT BULLS"
http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/20/obama-breed-specific-legislation_n_3785911.html?utm_hp_ref=dc&ir=DC

There will be a rally at the West Lawn of the US Capital in an effort to end discrimination (BSL/BDL) and abuse (dog Fighting) and by doing so, create safe and humane communities for humans and pets.  We will offer solutions to ending what has become a national epidemic, dog fighting. To "ban" or "abolish" a breed is far from an intelligent solution but rather a quick fix to what is an obvious social issue.  Now, more than ever before, broken young people all over this country are committing heinous acts against these innocent beings. Time and time again, studies prove the common denominator in prisoners from all walks of life who have committed an array of crimes is animal abuse. Sociopathic behavior toward animals is directly related to humans and currently the breed being victimized by this abuse more than any other breed on earth, are Pit Bull Terriers.  Loving, gentle, strong, compassionate, smart dogs who are being shot full of steroids, mutilated, fed gun powder among other things and forced to fight.  The abuse of animals is not only an ethical treatment of animals issue but rather an obvious reflection of a broken society, which can no longer be ignored.   Lawmakers must recognize that discrimination enshrined in law is wrong and time is NOW for to give the millions of voiceless victims a voice and the chance to finally be heard. 

www.standupforpits.us

***This is a HUMAN ONLY event.  Dogs are NOT allowed***

The purpose of this event is to educate, bring awareness and in doing so end discrimination and abuse.  Having dogs there will not accomplish or contribute to this goal in any way.  If dogs could over turn laws they would have done it a long time ago.  It's up to US to BE THEIR VOICE and to be responsible and respectful of the US CAPITAL grounds. This is a national opportunity to represent them in a positive way and enlighten others about the truth.


PLEASE READ-PLEASE READ-PLEASE READ-PLEASE READ
*******VERY IMPORTANT THINGS TO REMEMBER********

1. BE COOL.  ALWAYS...NO MATTER WHAT...BE COOL.

2. BSL and our Pibbles are a very emotional subject for Pibble owners.  People who know nothing about the breed except what they've read in the media, which is usually negative, can be extremely frustrating but when encountering people who are spewing negative at you, ALWAYS remember point #1.

3. Remember that people will be forming their opinions about Pit bulls and Pit bull owners based on their interaction with YOU.
Please don't be the screaming and swearing lunatic. Be the gentle, intelligent voice.  In other words...be like our beautiful Pibbles. Full of , love, patience and kindness.  Be cool. Always be cool.

4. You won't be able to change the opinion of every single person you meet, and that's okay.
Handle yourself with grace and dignity and the change will happen one person at a time.   Knowledge is power.  The more you know....the more power you have. EDUCATE, EDUCATE, EDUCATE!!!

5. Familiarize yourself with the actual data facts about BSL.
If you can't remember them off of the top of your head during a discussion, it's pretty handy to have links printed out to hand to them. If that's not an option, you could politely state that you hear their point and would like to send them actual statistical study facts for them to review. Offer to email them some information to review; ask for their email to do so, or offer yours.

6. Don't go looking for a fight.
Ask "Why do you feel this way?"  Then...listen to them.  This is how dialogue with a positive outcome can happen. People respond better to you asking questions, it shows you care about what's important to them. You'll be more effective at offering the appropriate information if you understand how they formed their opinion.

7. Don't fight a losing battle.
If someone is really entrenched in their beliefs and refuses to hear you...just wrap it up with "I understand if you won't change your opinion. I hear you and I'm really sorry you feel that way. Thanks for you time”. Remember, be cool. Always be cool.


We need each and every single one of you. YOU are what is vital to making this event a success not your Pibble. This is a giant opportunity and TOGETHER we can make history.
458355347587097.name: ONE MILLION PIBBLE MARCH ON WASHINGTON DC

*In English below


”I'm feeling hungry today.” -Francis J. Underwood

Us too! KY Economicsillakin on nälkä kasvanut syödessä, sillä nyt ladotaan tiskiin huikaisevin opintomatka tähän mennessä!

Ensi syksynä sinulla on ainutlaatuinen mahdollisuus päästä tutustumaan maailman tärkeimpään supervaltaan, Yhdysvaltoihin, ja vieläpä sen vallan ytimessä, pääkaupunki Washington D.C.:ssä! 

Tämä kiehtova pääkaupunki hellii huomassaan muunmuassa Yhdysvaltain presidentin virka-asuntoa Valkoista taloa, Yhdyvaltain kongressia sekä Korkeinta oikeutta. Kivenheiton päässä sijaitsee myös Yhdysvaltain puolustusministeriö Pentagon.
Washington on päämaja paitsi kansalliselle johdolle, myös lukuisille kansainvälisille yrityksille ja instituutioille, joihin pääsemme opintomatkan aikana tutustumaan lähemmin; esimerkkeinä mainittakoon vaikkapa Maailman Pankki, The Carlyle Group, Fannie Mae ja Freedom House.

Vapaa-aikaa jää myös rutkasti, joten Capitol Hillin ja Pentagonin kierrosten sekä yritysekskujen lomassa opintomatkalaisilla on mahdollisuus tutustua muun muassa legendaarisiin Lincolnin ja Washingtonin muistomerkkeihin ja vierailla vaikkapa jossain Smithsonian Instituten monista arvostetuista museoista. Tiedonjanoisen oloa helpottaa maailman suurin kirjastokompleksi Library of Congress sekä Yhdysvaltain kansallisarkistot, joista löytyvät esimerkiksi Itsenäisyysjulistus, perustulaki sekä perusoikeuksien asiakirja Bill of Rights. Hieman kevyempää sisältöä kaipaaville D.C. tarjoaa korkealaatuiset ostosmahdollisuudet ja eläväiset ulkoilmatorit, yöelämää unohtamatta!

Loppuhuipennuksen matkalle antaa se, että pääsemme juhlimaan Halloweenia niin autenttisella tavalla kuin se suinkin on mahdollista, yankee-style, juhlan alkuperämaassa. Ehei, tämä ei ole kepponen, vaan totista totta! Koska haluamme tehdä päätöksen sinulle hyvin helpoksi, tarjoamme matkan 690 euron hyvin hemaisevaan hintaan, joka kattaa lennot, majoituksen, yritysekskursiot sekä Capitolin ja Pentagonin kierrokset. Joko alkoivat suupielet kostua? Niin meilläkin! Lähde siis mukaan toteamaan itse, onko elämä Capitol Hillillä yhtä armotonta kuin House of Cards antaa ymmärtää. Klikkaa attending, niin saat päivitykset matkaohjelmasta!

Matka sijoittuu ajalle 25.10. - 1.11.2014. Matkan hinta on 690€. Linkki ilmoittautumislomakkeeseen postataan tähän eventiin perjantaina 2.5.2014 kello 12. Ilmoittautuminen on auki sunnuntaihin 11.5.2014 klo 23:59 asti. Osallistujat valikoidaan motivaatiokirjeen perusteella, taloustieteen opiskelijoilla kuitenkin etusija. Matkalle pääsevät vahvistetaan sähköpostitse maanantaina 12.5. Matka maksetaan kolmessa erässä; ensimmäinen, toukokuun erä on 400€.

MITÄ: KY Economicsin opintomatka Washington D.C.:hen
MISSÄ: Washington D.C. & Virginia, USA
MILLOIN: 25.10. - 1.11.2014
KENELLE: Kaikki AYY:n jäsenet ovat tervetulleita, 16 motivoituneinta pääsee mukaan!
MITÄ MAKSAA: 690€
MILLOIN TOIMIA: Ilmo auki 2.5.2014 klo 12:00 – 11.5.2014 klo 23:59

Menossa mukana myös McKinsey & Co. http://www.mckinsey.com/ 


*“I’m feeling hungry today” –Francis J. Underwood 

Us too! KY Economics is reaching a whole new level by offering you the most magnificent study trip so far!
Next fall you have a unique chance to get to know the most important superpower of the world, the United States of America, at the very core of its power, in its capital of Washington D.C.!

In this sizzling capital you’ll find for example the official residence of Mr President, the White House, the U.S. Congress and the Supreme Court. Also the U.S. Department of Defence, Pentagon, is located just around the corner. Washington is not only the head of the national cord, but also the location of numerous international corporations and institutions that we’ll get closer acquainted during the study trip; World Bank, The Carlyle Group, Fannie Mae and Freedom house, just to mention a few.

There will be also plenty of free time so among the tours of the Hill and the company excursions you’ll have a chance to get to visit for example the legendary Lincoln memorial or Washington monument and even pop in to one of the many famous museums in the Smithsonian Institution. If you’re feeling inquisitive, you can visit the biggest library ensemble in the world, Library of Congress, and the national libraries of the U.S., where for example the Declaration of Independence, and Bill of Rights are located. When looking for something a bit less formal, D.C. offers also high quality shopping possibilities and lively night markets – and don’t forget the night life!

On top of the cake we’ll remind that we’ll get to celebrate Halloween as authentically as possible, yankee-style, where the whole thing was originally born. Nope, this ain’t a trick but the very truth! In order to make the decision very easy for you, we’re offering the trip at the very tasty price of 690€ which covers flights, accommodation, company excursions and the tours of Capitol Hill and Pentagon. Feeling thirsty yet? So are we! Hop on then to see whether life at the Capitol Hill is as ruthless as House of Cards implies. Click attending and you’ll stay up to date with the trip program! 

The trip will take place 25.10. – 1.11.2014. A link to the enrolment form will be posted to this event on Friday 2.5.2014 at 12 p.m. The enrolment will be open until Sunday 11.5.2014 23.59. Attendants will be selected based on a motivation letter, preferring economics students though. Confirmation for those admitted on the trip will be sent by email on Monday 12.5. Trip will be paid in three instalments, first instalment in May will be 400€.

WHAT: KY Economics Study trip to Washington D.C.
WHERE: Washington D.C. & Virginia, USA
WHEN: 25.10. – 1.11.2014
TO WHOM: All AYY members are welcome, the 16 most motivational will be selected to go!
WHAT IT COSTS: 690€
WHEN TO ACT: Enrolment open 2.5.2014 12:00 noon – 11.5.2014 23.59

Don't forget to check out our partner, McKinsey & Co. http://www.mckinsey.com/

Bourgeon's 4th Annual DC Student Arts Journalism Competition identifies and supports talented young arts journalists. The competition is now OPEN to undergraduate students in DC area colleges and universities. 

There is no fee to enter the competition. Submissions must be received by APRIL 30 in pdf or doc format to competition@dayeight.org. Only one submission per entrant will be accepted.

Competition FAQ's at:  http://bourgeononline.com/arts-journalism-challenge-faqs/

Five finalists, selected by the Bourgeon Editorial board, will have their work published in the magazine. A panel of professional critics will select a winner from the finalists. The award includes a $150 cash prize. 

In the first two years the jury has included: Michael O’Sullivan (Washington Post), Anne Midgette (Washington Post), Leonard Jacobs (Clyde Fitch Report, Backstage), Amanda Abrams (Washington City Paper), Robert Bettmann (Bourgeon), Elizabeth Grazioli (ArtSeeDC), and Lewis Segal (Los Angeles Times).

More information: http://bourgeononline.com/student-arts-journalism-challenge/ 

The Arts Journalism Challenge is a project of DAY EIGHT.

480896542011645.description:
Here in our nation's capital, some people's only reference to American Indians is the racist name of the Washington football team.  But American Indians are disproportionally affected by poverty, hunger, unemployment, homelessness, etc.  Despite what Washington football team owner Dan Snyder has said, these aren't just "unfortunate facts,” but are directly related to the expansion and development of American capitalism.   

Ever since Europeans came to this continent, there has been conflict between natives and non-natives.  American capitalism could not have developed into the power it is today without stolen land and the slaughter of American Indians.  This didn't happen without a fight, and there are stories throughout history of American Indians fighting back.  

American Indians are still fighting to this day. The Idle No More movement that started in Canada has reinvigorated a fight for indigenous rights in North America.  Now the Cowboy-Indian Alliance, an alliance of American Indians, ranchers, and farmers, is coming to D.C. April 22-27 to pressure the government to reject the Keystone XL pipeline, which would damage our lands in many ways.   

Come learn more about the fight for American Indians rights, both past and present, and how we can build solidarity for the fight to come.
480896542011645.location: La Casa, 3166 Mt. Pleasant St NW, Washington, DC
480896542011645.name: More than a Name: The Fight for American Indian Rights

490768451049716.description:
The Speed Traders Workshop

How Banks, Hedge and Mutual Funds and Brokers Battle Markets 'RIGGED' by Wall Street's 'Flash Boys', High-frequency Trading, Exchanges and Dark Pools

Course Director
Edgar Perez
Author of The Speed Traders and Knightmare on Wall Street

Global scrutiny of high-frequency trading and whether it gives some investors unfair advantage has intensified amid government probes and the March 31, 2014 publication of "Flash Boys" by Michael Lewis. While those examinations have focused mostly on U.S. equity markets, such as dark pools run by banks and broker-dealers and exchanges owned by companies including Nasdaq OMX, IntercontinentalExchange Group's NYSE Euronext and Bats Global Markets, high-frequency traders are active internationally in futures, FX and fixed income markets, as they also run multi-asset strategies.

High-frequency traders have been called many things, from emerging masters of the universe and market pioneers to exploiters, computer geeks, and even predators and thieves. Everyone in the business of investing has an opinion of speed traders, but how many really understand how they operate? The shadow people of the investing world, today's high-frequency traders have decidedly kept a low profile, until now.

The Speed Traders Workshop, the first and most comprehensive initiation to the world of high-frequency trading, opens the door to the secretive world of computerized low-latency trading, the most controversial form of investing today; in the name of protecting the algorithms they have spent so much time perfecting, speed traders almost never talk to the press and try to disclose as little as possible about how they operate.

The Speed Traders Workshop covers the latest research currently available and reveals how high-frequency trading players are operating in global markets and driving the development of electronic trading at breakneck speeds from the U.S. and Europe to Japan, India, and Brazil. The “flash crash”, the suspended BATS IPO, the botched Facebook IPO, Knight Capital's trading malfunction and NASDAQ's Flash Freeze are just a few of the milestones in the history of high-frequency trading that will be dissected with participants.

"Edgar Perez is THE expert on high-frequency trading."
Liz Claman, Anchor, FOX Business News 

"Perez illuminates the world of speed."
Brenda Jubin, Contributor, Seeking Alpha

"There is a new day in trading and speed is the key.
Edgar Perez is the poster child."
Eugene Steele, Managing Partner, Trading Rooms

Workshop Highlights

   * The first and most comprehensive global initiation to the world of high-frequency trading
   * Key enablers of high-frequency trading in the U.S., Europe and Asia
   * Strategies high-frequency traders leverage to find alpha in up and down markets
   * Techniques to detect and avoid high-frequency trading in the markets
   * Regulatory framework and initiatives for speed trading
   * Latest update on high-frequency trading in the world and current regulatory initiatives after the "flash crash" and Michael Lewis' "Flash Boys"
   * Up-to-date review of the future of high-frequency trading
   * Study materials developed by Edgar Perez, the author of the most popular books on the subject of high-frequency trading, The Speed Traders and Knightmare on Wall Street, commentator on Bloomberg, CNN, CNBC, FOX Business News and other business media, and a well-known presenter in conferences and seminars in America, Europe and Asia
490768451049716.name: The Speed Traders Workshop Washington DC, "How Banks, Hedge and Mutual Funds and Brokers Battle Markets 'RIGGED' by Wall Street's 'Flash Boys', High-frequency Trading, Exchanges and Dark Pools"

http://ssdp.org/events/2014-conference-lobby-day/

Over the course of three days every other fall, the SSDP network comes together to celebrate, learn, connect, and advocate at the SSDP Conference + Lobby Days. This year, SSDP2014 will bring more than 400 student members, alumni, and supporters to Washington, DC for our largest-ever gathering featuring:

*Educational programming. The core conference program will include prominent keynote speakers and panels addressing the hottest topics in policy, harm reduction, leadership, organizing, and advocacy.
*Awards Ceremony + Dance Party. SSDP recognizes outstanding network members with a biannual awards ceremony followed by a dance party.
*SSDP Job Fair. Students and alumni will have a unique opportunity to connect with drug policy reform organizations and legal marijuana-related businesses seeking to enhance their growing staffs with young people who are uniquely dedicated and already trained in leadership skills.
*Student Congress. Our annual student board member election and governing resolution process invites all SSDP members to participate in defining their SSDP.
*Lobby Days. Students, alumni, and network members will have a unique opportunity to lobby Members of Congress on a core issue for the SSDP network and other critical drug policy reforms with a team of like-minded advocates.
*And more. Alumni gatherings, regional meetups, networking meals, and other events offer nearly non-stop opportunities to connect with advocates and leaders of the drug policy reform movement!
510510122368864.name: Save the Date: SSDP's 2014 Conference + Lobby Day in Washington, DC!

Borgore (Asaf Borger) is an Israeli producer and DJ who in the last four years has pushed and broken the boundaries of dubstep as we know it successfully creating his own self titled genre of hardcore, Gorestep. Borgore destroys dancefloors with his heavy bass and dirty lyrics that keep his consistently sold out shows in a twerking frenzy of cake and sweat. Borgore knows how to bring out the fun, crazy and wild partier in all of us, and he does it without the violent and dark thrasher lyrics typically heard from his predecessors in heavy metal and rock groups.

Having risen to fame with chart successes such as ‘Let the Bass Kick’ and ‘Aftershock,’ Chuckie’s career has continued to trace an exponentially upward trajectory that has escalated him into a world-renowned figurehead and tastemaker. As a pioneer of the rapidly proliferating Dirty Dutch sound, which has burst on to the international stage with its fusion of big grooves and livewire synths, he has taken his diverse musical palette worldwide and continues to spread the Chuckie flavour with his explosive beats, impeccable mixing and inimitable charisma. Born in South America, Chuckie (real name Clyde Sergio Narain) later moved to The Netherlands where his passion for hip-hop and electronic music grew and eventually manifested itself in his decision to become a DJ and producer. His energetic mixing skills coupled with an ability to effortlessly blend different musical styles has made Chuckie one of the most in- demand DJs in the world.

CONNOR CRUISE brings a unique style to the decks, blending together big room house, EDM anthems, and an eclectic mix of other influences featuring the likes of Tiesto, Quintino, Knife Party, Tommy Trash and more. His upbeat sets have taken him around the world, deejaying at some of the most well-known nightclubs in the country, including Create (Los Angeles), Studio Paris (Chicago), Pacha (New York), and countless others; this year alone, he will have also played overseas in Guatemala, Panama, Spain, Germany, Singapore, Philippines and the Dominican Republic.

Cazzette may have been part of the Swedish EDM explosion of 2012, but they quickly distinguished themselves from Dada Life, Swedish House Mafia, and the rest of the competition when they announced their official debut would be the first ever released exclusively on a streaming music site. Members Sebastian Furrer and Alexander Björklund were two Stockholm producers who joined forces in 2011. After meeting manager Ash Pournouri, the three combined two of the favorite strains of dance music -- dubstep and house -- for a sound they called "dubhouse." Bootlegs of Swedish House Mafia and Kanye West tracks introduced their dubhouse to loyal EDM fans, and through Pournouri, they were able to bring this sound to the masses when they made their official debut in 2011 with a remix of Avicii's single "Sweet Dreams." They were signed by Avicii's and Pournouri's management company, At Night Management, that same year and hired to do an official remix of Swedish House Mafia's "Save the World." Released at the same time, their bootleg remix of Adele's "Set Fire to the Rain" was nearly as significant, climbing to number one on Hype Machine's chart of trending downloads. Gigs at XS and Surrender in Las Vegas, Ushuaia in Ibiza, and Radio City Music Hall in New York City followed, along with main stage slots at festivals like Creamfields, Ultra, and Tomorrowland. In 2012, they released their single "Beam Me Up," and the Strictly Rhythm label collected some of their best remixes and productions on the mix CD Strictly Cazzette. That same year, they made headlines when their debut EP became the first major debut issued exclusively to a streaming music site. The EP, titled Eject, appeared on Spotify in November of that year.

530418497074038.description:
Trans-forming Love is a day of education, dialogue, and prayer to better understand transgender issues from a Catholic perspective.

The goal of the day is to dispel myths and stereotypes about transgender people by gaining sound information from the scientific community and from transgender people themselves. Their experiences will also be explored in the light of faith and spirituality.

The day includes presentations on gender identity development, personal perspectives, legal considerations, and spiritual dimensions. There will be Q & A sessions, small group discussions, and informational handouts.

Speakers will include:

Michael Hendricks, Ph.D. holds his doctorate in clinical psychology from The American University. He is a fellow of the American Academy of Clinical Psychology. He is the current President of the American Psychological Association's Division 44, the Society for the Psychological Study of LGBT Issues. He is a partner at the Washington Psychological Center in DC, and teaches graduate-level courses at The Catholic University of America. Dr. Hendricks has worked with transgender individuals for nearly 15 years.

Hilary Howes is a Catholic transgender woman, who has been married for 36 years. She authored the article, "To Be or Not to Be: A Catholic Transexual Speaks," which describes her converstion to Catholicism and her gender transition. Hilary is involved with several transgender rights organizations and is a member of the Pacific School of Religion - Trans Roundtable. Hilary spoke at the New Ways Ministry national symposium on Catholic LGBT issues in March 2012.

Pre-registration is required, along with a $25 donation (more if you can, less if you cannot). To register, contact New Ways Ministry at (301) 277-5674.
530418497074038.location: Centro Maria 650 Jackson Street NE Washington, DC 20017
530418497074038.name: Trans-forming Love in DC

542082125911563.description:
The Center for Poetic Thought
716 Monroe Street NE
Studio 25

(Photo of The Crying Tree by Patssi Valdez)

FEATURING Carmen Calatayud, Celeste Doaks and Shannon Ward

While male poets have received recognition for popularizing the
category of ekphrastic poetry, multiple women writers have heavily influenced the genre as well. Women such as Elizabeth Bishop, Adrienne Rich, Anne Sexton, Valerie Martinez, Rita Dove, Natasha Trethewey and Stevie Smith are just a few impressive female voices who've written ekphrasis. And often women employ what bell hooks refers to in film theory as an "oppositional gaze" when writing about art. Hooks believes, "Spaces of agency exist ...wherein we can both interrogate the gaze of the other
but also look back, and at one another, naming what we see." This is the ultimate goal when women writers pen art poems.

To kick off National Poetry Month three women Carmen Calatayud, Celeste Doaks and Shannon Ward will carry on the tradition by presenting their ekphrastic poems, and the visual images that inspired them.

Join us as we enjoy some wonderful poetry and have an engaging dialogue about classic and contemporary art!
542082125911563.name: DC POETRY READING: 3 Women and their Ekphrastic Poems

551209024977851.description:
Join the DC Trainers Network for the May Skillshare: Theater of the Oppressed

Theater of the Oppressed is a theoretical framework and set of techniques developed by Brazilian director, artist and activist Augusto Boal. Recognizing that humans have a unique ability to take action in the world while simultaneously observing themselves in action, Boal believed that the human was a self-contained theater, actor and spectator in one. Because we can observe ourselves in action, we can amend, adjust and alter our actions to have different impact and to change our world.
Theatre of the Oppressed engages people in discovery, critical reflection and dialogue and the process of liberation.

May facilitator Annalisa Dias has taught theater of the oppressed nationally and internationally. During this skillshare she'll share games and techniques designed to help inspire the practice of freedom. 
                                               ***

The DC Trainers Network monthly skillshare is a structured, interactive space where people can share skills and gain confidence in their training abilities and everybody is both a teacher and a learner. It strives to provide an inclusive practice space to experiment with different approaches for learning and teaching. This skillshare seeks to strengthen the DC activist community’s ability to meet the needs of progressive social movements.
551209024977851.location: St. Stephen & the Incarnation Episcopal Church - Washington, DC
551209024977851.name: Theater of the Oppressed: May Skillshare

Modern day record minstrel, Mark Farina, has thrilled crowds globally, entertaining over 1 million fans per year. As one of the most ubiquitous DJs in Dance Music, Farina's known for both his unique style of mixing Jazz, Downtempo and House Music as well as being the creator of Mushroom Jazz: West Coast jazzy, organic productions combined with East Coast Hip-Hop, Urban beats. 

Drawing from his vibrant youth, which included being a trumpet player in marching band, a drummer in a nu wave cover band and a guest DJ, Friday nights on WNUR (Chicago), Mark found his passion for the luscious world of vinyl, turntables and nightclubs. At 16, Farina began his DJ career as a resident at Chicago's underage mecca, Medusa's. At the same time Mark joined forces with emerging DJs Derrick Carter and Chris Nazuka then moved into a loft space called Rednail. Rednail became infamous not only for raucous parties but also as the home to the trio's first productions under the moniker, Symbols & Instruments. Their release,"MOOD," sold 35,000 copies in the US & UK and is credited as "the first ambient house track." 

Voted as one of the top DJ's in the world by URB, MUZIK and BPM magazines, Mark Farina's taste making skills continue to turn the heads of seasoned Dance Music veterans as well as newcomers to the scene.
556546954441740.name: Mark Farina | Washington DC

574025236038253.description:
BloomBars presents, the most watched Brazilian documentary of 2013...

Elena (2012, 80 min), by Petra Costa - Intimate in style, ELENA delves into the abyss of one family’s drama, revealing at once the inspiration that can be born from tragedy. Elena, a young Brazilian woman, moves to New York with the same dream as her mother had, to become a movie actress. She leaves behind her childhood spent in hiding during the years of the military dictatorship. She also leaves Petra, her seven-year-old sister. Two decades later, Petra also becomes an actress and goes to New York in search of Elena. She only has a few clues about her: home movies, newspaper clippings, a diary and letters. ELENA is a film about the persistence of those memories, the irreversibility of that loss, and the impact the absence of her sister had on the seven-year-old girl. (In Portuguese with English subtitles). (http://tinyurl.com/elena-trailer).

Our screening will be followed by Q&A discussion with director Petra Costa, Prof. Renato Alvim of American University and staff from the Embassy of Brazil.

Bloombars, in association with the Washington Portuguese Language Meetup (WPLM), is proud to present monthly films which highlight the best of Lusophone culture.

*Suggested Donation: $10. Proceeds support both WPLM and BloomBars. Free organic popcorn.

BloomScreen Indie Film Night is a weekly series of independent and foreign films, accompanied by discussions with filmmakers, experts and other guests.

581433991952025.description:
The FORT KNOX FIVE have spent the last decade as a leading force in the international funk and breaks scene. Having released an arsenal of floor rocking original music and remixes, the FORT KNOX FIVE has the midas touch for producing heavy hitting records.

The FORT KNOX FIVE established Fort Knox Recordings in 2003 to release party-rocking music that crosses tempos and defies genres. Their world renowned ‘Fort Knox Sound’ has overtaken dance-floors with its distinct interweaving of live instrumentation with funky electronic breakbeats. 

FK5’s talent for organic hooks has made them highly sought after producer/remixers, and landed them in the prestigious URB Next 100. They have dozens of remixes to their credit, including monster remixes for the legendary Tito Puente, Louis Armstrong, and Bob Marley. Further cementing the FORT KNOX FIVE’S production reputation, Afrika Bambaataa—the godfather of hip-hop—has recruited them numerous times to produce tracks. Their video for the song Shift featuring Afrika Bambaataa & Mustafa Akbar was called “groundbreaking” by Spinner. Their songs have consistently broken the Itunes &  Beatport Top 10 Charts in multiple genres, Including reaching #1 positions in Breaks, Reggae, and Chillout on Beatport.

The FORT KNOX FIVE’S music has been featured predominately in numerous high profile films, television shows, ad campaigns, and video games. FK5 music can be found in hit TV shows like Fox’s Fringe, and the Oscar Winning Documentary The Cove. They are also no strangers to the world of video game music. There music has been featured in dozens of monster video games like EA Sports NBA Live, Tiger Woods PGA Tour, and Need For Speed. Recently they completed a new original Fort Knox Five music composition called ‘Stand Up’ for the feature film, Stand Up Guys, staring Al Pacino, Christopher Walken, and Alan Arkin.

As DJs, they know how to rock parties with infectious grooves that effortlessly move from funk, reggae, and hip-hop to prime time 4/4 beats & breaks. Their unique Turntable DJ sets have proven irresistible to clubgoers worldwide. They have performed on 5 continents, and in over 30 different countries, playing some of the largest festivals and club nights around the globe. The Fort Knox Five have toured and performed alongside major artists like The Beastie Boys, Snoop Dogg, Public Enemy, James Brown, Jurassic 5, Z Trip, Diplo, A Trak, Craze, A Skillz, Krafty Kuts, Stanton Warriors, Bassnectar, Skrillex, and London Electricity to name a few. Forget about tempos and genres – let the Fort Knox Five take you back to the roots and unite all music from the funk, soul, jazz, dub, hip hop, reggae, and electronic generations. 

The FORT KNOX FIVE will be touring this spring and summer in support of their recent 10 Years of Fort Knox Five compilation. This will lead up to their upcoming album release in Winter of 2013/14

587528717990745.description:
Beyond Darkness, there is always Light; How deep are you willing to search?

THE MISSION

The ABYSS, presented by Assassins DC and Urban Artistry, offers a new perspective on producing house dance experiences, by focusing on and honoring the most essential elements of house dance culture: the human spirit and cypher participation. We will be conducting qualifiers in cities around the United States culminating in the final ABYSS Cypher Session at the International Soul Society Festival in Washington DC on April 2014. In the process, we hope to inspire a culture of honesty, integrity, self-discovery, and fearlessness, along every participant's journey to evolved artistry.

THE CONCEPT

At the start of any house dance experience are the layers within the sound we call house music. These layers are engineered to inspire free movement, cultural enlightenment and artistic growth. Often, unwanted darkness settles on these layers; a darkness made up of doubt, insecurity, fear, and perceived judgment. However, the human spirit's ability to overcome these inner walls, obstacles, and layers is inevitable… if you believe in yourself. The ABYSS celebrates the cypher as the ultimate space to explore these layers, share these layers, and create more layers, within ourselves and with each other. And so, the ABYSS calls upon Warriors of Light—dancers willing to go deep, to trust their guts, and explore the depths of the layers in and out of the cypher.

"Only when we are brave enough to explore the darkness will we discover the infinite power of our light.” Brown

-Brené Brown

THE FORMAT

PRE-SELECTION

The pre-selection round will consist of 1-on-1 showcases, with each participant getting one, un-timed run.

Dancers, one dancer, or neither dancer will advance.

An Advisory Committee, made up of the event organizers, local House Dance professionals will choose 12 dancers to advance to the cypher session.

THE CYPHER SESSION

The cypher session will be a one-hour cypher of uninterrupted exchanges between the chosen dozen from pre-selection.

JUDGING

The 12 finalists will choose a winner amongst themselves. Each dancer will have one vote, but cannot vote for himself/herself.

The dancer with a majority of the votes will be the winner.

Should there be a tie(s), those receiving the highest number of votes will be given a chance to concede to the dancer(s) that they believe is the winner. If the dancers choose to continue, they will return to the cypher for an additional 30 minutes or the final exchange. During this final exchange, all dancers have the right to concede and proclaim the opponent(s) the winner. If no one concedes during or after the final exchange, the Advisory

Committee will choose a winner from those remaining, based on technique, musicality, originality and artistry.

AWARDING

The Final Cypher Champion will receive a personalized handmade adornment, handwritten recognition as THE ABYSS 2014 Warrior of Light and $1000.
587528717990745.name: THE ABYSS: A House Dance Experience in Washington DC "The Final Cypher Session"

Annual Montgomery County Republican Parties Lincoln Reagan Dinner - Keynote Speaker Gov. Jim Gilmore

Jim Gilmore served as the 68th governor of Virginia from 1998 to 2002.  Gilmore gained national prominence during his campaign and governorship by advocating conservative policies that directly addressed the daily concerns of working men and women in every Virginia community.

While his election ushered in the first complete GOP control of the executive branch of Virginia state government, Gilmore’s legacy of nearly two decades of public service is highlighted by significant policy work on the major issues of taxation and homeland security and by a determined focus to bring people together from different beliefs and backgrounds.

Born and raised in Richmond, Gilmore first won elected office as a local prosecutor in Henrico County, Virginia in 1987.  He then went on to win statewide elected office in 1993 as attorney general of Virginia.  Then-Attorney General Gilmore led a nationwide effort to stop arson against African-American churches.  He also took actions to improve consumer protection, cut down on Medicaid fraud and enhance public safety.

601174349952345.description:
Apr 03 Social Sound proudly presents.....
FORT KNOX FIVE - Washington DC / Fort Knox Recordings
*Shambhala & Burning Man Headliner*

The FORT KNOX FIVE is a leading force in the international funk and breaks scene. Having released an arsenal of floor rocking original music and remixes, the FORT KNOX FIVE has the midas touch for producing heavy hitting records.
The FORT KNOX FIVE established Fort Knox Recordings in 2003 to release party-rocking music that crosses tempos and defies genres. Their world renowned ‘Fort Knox Sound’ has overtaken dance-floors with its distinct interweaving of live instrumentation with funky electronic breakbeats.
FK5’s talent for organic hooks has made them highly sought after producer/remixers, and landed them in the prestigious URB Next 100. They have dozens of remixes to their credit, including monster remixes for legendary artists. Tito Puente, Louis Armstrong, and Bob Marley. Further cementing the FORT KNOX FIVE’s production reputation, Afrika Bambaataa—the godfather of hip-hop—has recruited them numerous times to produce tracks. Their songs have consistently broken the Beatport Top 10 Charts in multiple genres, fetching #1 positions in Breaks, Reggae, and Chillout.

Their music has been featured predominately in numerous high profile films, television shows, ad campaigns, and video games. FK5 music can be found in hit TV shows like Fox’s Fringe, and the Oscar Winning Documentary The Cove. They are also no strangers to the world of video game music. There music has been featured in dozens of monster video games like EA Sports NBA Live, Tiger Woods PGA Tour, and Need For Speed. Recently they completed a new original Fort Knox Five music composition called ‘Stand Up’ for the upcoming feature film, Stand Up Guys, staring Al Pacino, Christopher Walken, and Alan Arkin.

As DJs, they know how to rock parties with infectious grooves that effortlessly move from funk, reggae, and hip-hop to prime time 4/4 beats & breaks. Their unique DJ sets have proven irresistible to clubgoers worldwide. They have performed on 5 continents, and in over 30 different countries, playing some of the largest festivals and club nights around the globe. The Fort Knox Five have toured and performed alongside major artists like The Beastie Boys, Snoop Dogg, Public Enemy, James Brown, Jurassic 5, Z Trip, Diplo, A Trak, Craze, A Skillz, Krafty Kuts, Stanton Warriors, Bassnectar, Skrillex, and London Electricity to name a few. Forget about tempos and genres – let the Fort Knox Five take you back to the roots and unite all music from the funk, soul, jazz, dub, hip hop, reggae, and electronic generations.

605610522863751.description:
ENTC offers a clear-cut solution to the crisis in Ethiopia 
 
 
The human rights atrocities, incitement of hostilities between ethnic groups, and systemic corruption 
has become so routine in Ethiopia that many people are accepting them as normal. Others are ignoring 
the problems because they have succumbed to hopelessness. Ethiopian National Transitional Council 
(ENTC) believes that losing hope is not an option. The recent ethnic cleansing campaign against Amhara 
farmers in western Ethiopia, the brutal crackdown of peaceful Muslim protesters who are demanding 
religious freedom, the arrest of Arena Tigray party members in Tigray, mass arrest of Oromo youth and 
civilians in Arba Minch, and the continued detentions of journalists, political party leaders and members, 
and religious leaders can all be stopped if freedom loving Ethiopians come together and offer the people 
of Ethiopia an alternative to the ethnic apartheid regime. 
Removing the TPLF regime and replacing it with an all-inclusive transitional government is a clear-cut 
solution to the political, economic and social crises that have engulfed our country. 
The recent nation-wide efforts by UDJ and Semayawi parties to mobilize Ethiopians to assert their 
freedom are positive steps. ENTC fully supports their endeavours. ENTC is also pleased with the Ethiopian 
Muslim’s peaceful and courageous struggle to stop the TPLF regime’s interference in religious affairs. 
The logical extension to the efforts that are being made by Ethiopian pro-democracy forces is coming up 
with an alternative system of governance in Ethiopia. To help facilitate such process, ENTC has been 
holding consultative conferences in various cities since July 2012. 
ENTC will hold an important town hall meeting April 13, 2014 in Washington DC where prominent 
scholars, representatives of political and civic groups and religious leaders will discuss their vision on 
removing and replacing the regime in Ethiopia through a unified struggle. 
Guest speakers include religious leaders Abune Philipos and Sheik Khalid Mohammed; Ustaz Haji Najib, 
Aba Gebreselassie Tibebu, Prof. Alemayehu Gebremariam, Dr Kassa Kebede, Journalist Abebe Gelaw and 
ENTC speaker Ato Sileshi Tilahun. 
ENTC cordially invites all patriotic Ethiopians in the Washington DC area to participate in this important 
town hall meeting. 
Time/Date: Sunday, April 13, 2014, at 1:30 PM 
Place: Sheraton Pentagon City, 900 S. Orme Street, Arlington VA (Next to Dama Restaurant) 
 
ENTC leadership

አካባቢ የሚኖሩ ሰላማዊ ዜጎችን በጅምላ ማሰር፤ ለረጅም ጊዜ የሀይማኖት መሪዎችን፣ ጋዜጠኞችንና የፖለቲካ ድርጅት 
መሪዎችን በእስር ማቆየት፤ እነኝህ ድርጊቶች ሊቆሙ የሚችሉት ነፃነትን የሚሹ ኢትዮጵያውያን ትብብር በመፍጠር 
ለኢትዮጵያ ሕዝብ ከእዚህ ዘረኛ የአፓርታይድ አገዛዝ የተሻለ አማራጭ ሲያቀርቡ ነው። 
 
የህወሀት ሥርአትን በማስወገድ ሁሉን አቀፍ የሆነ ህዝባዊ የሽግግር መንግሥት ማቋቋም ሀገራችንን ጠፍንጐ ከያዛት 
የፖለቲካ፤ ኢኮኖሚና ማህበራዊ ቀውስ ነፃ የሚያወጣ ግልፅ መፍትሄ ነው። 
 
በቅርቡ በአንድነትና በሰማያዊ ፓርቲ እየተደረገ ያለው ሀገር አቀፍ የሆነ ኢትዮጵያውያንን የማስተባበርና የመታገል 
እንቅስቃሴ ኢትዮጵያውያን ለነፃነታቸው ለሚደርጉት ትግል አዎንታዊ እርምጃ ነው። የኢትዮጵያ ብሔራዊ የሽግግር ምክር 
ቤት ይህንን ታላቅ ጥረት ሙሉ በሙሉ ይደግፋል። በተጨማሪም የሽግግር ምክር ቤቱ ድምፃችን ይሰማ በሚያደርገው 
እንቅስቃሴና የኢትዮጵያ ሙስሊም ሀይማኖት ተከታይ ወገኖቻችን፤ የህወሀት አገዛዝ የሚያደርገውን የሀይማኖት ጣልቃ 
ገብነትን ለማስቆም የሚያካሂዱትን ቁርጠኝነት የተሞላበት የሰላማዊ እንቅስቃሴ ያደንቃል። 
 
የእነኚህ ጥረቶች ቀጣይ የአመክንዮ እርምጃ ሁሉም የኢትዮጵያ ዴሞክራሲያዊ ኃይሎች ተባብረው ለኢትዮጵያ ሕዝብ 
የተሻለ ተተኪ የአማራጭ መፍትሄ ማቅረብ ነው። ይህንን ሂደት ለማስተባበርና ለማመቻቸት የሽግግር ምክር ቤቱ ከጉዳዩ 
ጋር ተያያዥ የሆኑ የምክክር ስብሰባዎችን ላለፉት ሁለት ዓመታት በተለያዩ ከተማዎች አካሂዷል። 
 
የኢትዮጵያ ብሔራዊ የሽግግር ምክር ቤት በሚቀጥለው ሚያዝያ 5 ቀን 2006 (April 13, 2014) ወቅታዊና በጣም አስፈላጊ 
ህዝባዊ ስብሰባ በዋሽንግተን ዲሲ ከተማ ያካሂዳል። በእዚህም ስብሰባ ላይ የሃይማኖት መሪዎች፣ ታዋቂ ምሁራን፣ 
የፖለቲካና የሲቪክ ማሕበራት መሪዎች በተባበረ ትግል የህዋት ስርአትን በማስወገድና በመተካት፤ እንዲሁም በኢትዮጵያ 
ሁሉን አቀፍ ህዝባዊ የሽግግር መንግስት ምስረታን መሰረት በመጣል ሂደት ላይ የተለያዩ የህብረተሰብ ክፍሎች ተሳትፎና 
ሚና ምን መምሰል እንዳለበት ማብራሪያና ትንታኔ ይሰጣሉሉ። 
 
የዕለቱ ተናጋሪዎች አቡነ ፊሊፖስ፣ ሼክ ኻሊድ መሀመድ፣ ኡስታዝ ሀጂ ነጂብ፣ አባ ገብረሥላሴ ጥበቡ፣ ፕ/ር አለማየሁ 
ገብረማርያም፣ ዶ/ር ካሣ ከበደ፣ ጋዜጠኛ አበበ ገላውና የሽግግር ምክር ቤቱ አፈ ጉባዔ አቶ ስለሺ ጥላሁን ይሆናሉ። 
 
የኢትዮጵያ ብሔራዊ የሽግግር ምክር ቤት በዋሽንግተን ዲሲ ከተማ አካባቢ ለሚገኙ ሀገር ወዳድ ኢትዮጵያውያን በዚህ 
ህዝባዊ ስብሰባ ላይ እንዲገኙ በትሕትና ይጋብዛል። 
 
ቀንና ሰዓት፡ እሁድ ሚያዝያ 5 ቀን 2006 (ሰባት ተኩል)

The Doctor is back!!!!! It is Cherry Pitz’s Birthday and the one thing she is sure of is that the Doctor is going to make an. But the Doctor is less then thrilled as he can’t figure out why the Tardis keeps bringing him back to Cherry’s birthday - 80 consecutive days in a row! TWO SHOWS!  9:15 and 11:30.

Thrilled to be making their DC debut, Cherry Pitz and Joe the Shark present a burlesque tribute to the beloved BBC series, Doctor Who! Hotsy Totsy Burlesque is a New York based episodic, burlesque show featuring a different script each month and a rotating cast every 4th Wednesday of the month at New York’s premiere burlesque venue The Slipper Room. Past shows include tributes to Mad Men, Game of Thrones, Big Lebowski and Star Wars 1978 Holiday Special, Star Trek and The Hitchhikers Guide To The Galaxy. 608480975895135.description:
Join us at G-FEST 2014, our signature event! G-FEST promotes diversity and educates participants about world languages and cultures. Meet embassies, cultural organizations, performance groups, our Teaching Fellows and other GLNers as they represent their countries’ cultures and traditions through booths, performances, language lessons and games

Last year, during G-FEST 2013 we represented more than 20 countries, featured 6 cultural performances and attracted more than 500 guests. G-FEST 2014 will be bigger, better and even more fun! Here's a taste of what we are planning:

- Country Cultural Booths: embassies from around the world and various cultural organizations will showcase their cultures at our Cultural Booths. Featured countries include Azerbaijan, Bangladesh, Haiti, Honduras, Georgia, Saudi Arabia, Slovenia, Tanzania, Uzbekistan and many more!

- Cultural Performances: Traditional song and dance, including Eastern European folk dancing, Taiku, Bhangra dances, Korean fusion dance, Argentine tango and more!

- Language Lessons: Want to window shop for a new language? Swing by our 15-minute lesson demos, sample a language, and meet our Teaching Fellows. 

- GLN Raffle: Enter our raffle for a chance to win awesome prizes including gift cards from local restaurants, theaters, museums, yoga studios, gyms, and more!

G-GEST 2014 is open to the public and FREE of charge for visitors and participating organizations. Get your free ticket via Eventbrite:

http://www.eventbrite.com/e/g-fest-2014-global-languages-and-cultures-festival-tickets-10970624433?aff=efbevent
608480975895135.location: NYU Washington DC's Constance Milstein and Family Global Academic Center, 1307 L Street Northwest, Washington, DC, US
608480975895135.name: G-FEST 2014 (Global Languages and Cultures Festival)

Calling all RV owners!! Parents March Against Prohibition is scheduled for October 15, 2014.  

Let's hitch up and caravan across the country to add our bodies to the march! 

We can rideshare and caravan starting from California (where I will be), Oregon, and Washington, and picking up new RVers as we cross into their territory. 

This idea just this moment popped into my head, so there's a lot of fleshing out and planning to be done... so please feel free to add your input here in the event!!

Shepherdstown, WV--The Shepherd University's Office of Multicultural Affairs and Performing Arts Series will present the Gay Men's Chorus of Washington D.C. (GMCW) Saturday, March 22 at 8 p.m. at the Frank Center theater.

GMCW will perform its new program "Passion." It is an evening for all romantics and features beloved works that have touched the heart and stirred the passion of generations, with songs ranging from Dolly Parton's "I Will Always Love You" and the Righteous Brothers' "Unchained Melody" to songs from Broadway and opera including "Miss Saigon" and "La Traviata."

Now it its 33rd season, the GMCW is dedicated to both artistic excellence and social justice education. It has more than 275 singing members, two select vocal ensembles, 100 support volunteers, more than 800 subscribers, 500 donors, and an annual audience of more than 12,000 people. The chorus has performed at the White House, the John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts, Carnegie Hall, Symphony Hall in Boston, presidential inauguration celebrations, and more.

Tickets are available at the Shepherd University Bookstore. Tickets are $15 for general public, $10 for seniors and Shepherd staff, $5 for children, and free for Shepherd students with a valid Rambler ID. For tickets, call 304-876-5219 or go to www.shepherd.edu.

617772554974896.description:
Please join local PETA supporters in speaking out against the Canadian Seal Slaughter. http://www.canadasshame.com/

During the slaughter, tens of thousands of baby seals have their heads bashed in or are shot. Sealers hook seals in the eyes, cheeks, or mouth and drag them across the ice, often while they're still conscious. This slaughter continues, even though the market for seal products has all but disappeared: The U.S., the European Union, and Russia—which had been importing 95 percent of Canadian seal pelts—have all banned seal fur.	

To learn more, watch this video about the Canadian seal slaughter. http://www.peta.org/videos/canadas-shame

When: Thursday, April 10, 11:45 a.m.–1:00 p.m.

Where: Embassy of Canada, 501 Pennsylvania Ave NW, Washington, DC 20001; https://goo.gl/maps/QBBGH 

Contact: Ashley at ashleyb@peta.org or 757-274-9675 or on Facebook https: https://www.facebook.com/ashleyallisonbyrne

Posters and leaflets will be provided. Note that reserved parking will not be available, and please be prepared for the weather. Outreach events are a fun and effective way to help animals as well as meet local advocates, so before you go, check out PETA's outreach tips http://www.mediapeta.com/peta/PDF/tips_for_PETA_activists.pdf and be sure to invite everyone you know. 

If you can't make it, you can still take action by asking Canada to end the cruel slaughter. https://secure.peta.org/site/Advocacy?cmd=display&page=UserAction&id=4119&autologin=true
617772554974896.name: Washington, DC: Tell Canada to end its shameful seal slaughter

624820987602636.description:
Please join me for a Ba'al Shem Tov Seudah hosted by my friends Shalom and Deborah.  

The Baal-Shem-Tov, (or "BST" to his friends,) the famous traveling mystic who founded the early Hasidic movement in the 1700's, instituted the custom of a special meal to be eaten by his descendants on the last afternoon of Pesach. I inherited this tradition and invite you to share it with me this year.  We will tell the story of BST's attempt to go to Israel (because he thought it would bring the messiah) and how he was miraculously saved during the journey. We will also eat matza balls (because that has something to do with the story). Aside from this central story-telling, we will also get to hear other stories as folks bring them: stories of the Baal-Shem-Tov, stories of Rav Nachman of Breslov (his great-grandson), or any of the other thousands of classics that make up the Hasidic story-telling tradition.

The schedule for the evening will be as follows (feel free to come for some or all): 
5pm - Learning with Shalom 
6pm - Mincha
6:30pm - Ba'al Shem Tov Seudah
The arrival of Moshiach is scheduled for sometime after havdalah
 
People should feel free to bring packaged k-for-p food or fresh (unwaxed and uncut) produce, but food will be provided.  If people want to help set up, please arrive at 4:30pm.   Volunteers to come over and help cook in advance are appreciated.   RSVPs are appreciated but not required, so we have a sense of how much to cook.

633477090033654.description:
Typically the 4th of July is celebrated with a family barbecue and a nice local fireworks show. But in lieu of the repetitious I would like to suggest an alternative. An occupation so to speak.

  On November the 5th 2013 a non partisan, leaderless movement called the Million Mask March brought together Americans from many different political backgrounds without any infighting to peacefully petition the government for a redress of grievances.  I'm suggesting an occupation of Washington until those grievances are heard, acknowledged and fixed.  We have without any shadow of a doubt lost our freedoms and our bill of rights is all but gone, erased and overridden by new laws like NDAA and the Patriot act in the interest of national security to keep us safe from terrorism

Benjamin Franklin once said ''Those who would sell our freedoms for security deserve neither''. I agree with Benjamin Franklin and believe the proponents of these new unconstitutional bills do not deserve freedom but a lifetime sentence in a federal penitentiary.

One grievance in particular has undermined our democracy and our republic for a little over a hundred years now. The Federal Reserve is a private bank that has been drowning our country in debt for the benefit of a few. Woodrow Wilson even expressed grief for signing the federal reserve act stating “I am a most unhappy man. I have unwittingly ruined my country. A great industrial nation is controlled by its system of credit. Our system of credit is concentrated. The growth of the nation, therefore, and all our activities are in the hands of a few men. We have come to be one of the worst ruled, one of the most completely controlled and dominated Governments in the civilized world - no longer a Government by free opinion, no longer a Government by conviction and the vote of the majority, but a Government by the opinion and duress of a small group of dominant men.”

 Thomas Jefferson said ''I believe that banking institutions are more dangerous to our liberties than standing armies. If the american people ever allow private banks to control the issue of their currency, first by inflation then by deflation, the banks and corporations that grow up around them will deprive the people of all property until their children wake up homeless on the continent their fathers conquered. The issuing power should be taken from the banks and restored to the people, to whom it properly belongs.''

The founders of this nation warned us of the dangers of a central private bank and the apathy of the people towards policy in our govt. Their worst fears have come to fruition and have all but destroyed this country. The american people are down...but not out. We will not go quietly into the night. We will not stand by any longer and see this country of ours and our freedom turn to tyranny. We will fight for what is right and what is ours

I ask you the american people to stand beside us. Starting this July 4th we will occupy our capitol. I expect there will be few at first. But our continued presence in the capitol will show others they are not alone, and before long more will join.  If you are up to your ears in debt, If you are tired and hungry and you see the crimes of this government as we see it then i ask that you join us

Be prepared to accept everybody. Remember that no religious or political belief is inherently evil, they are just tools that we as a society use and that it is how we use and react to these tools that defines us and gives us our morality

Meet at the Washington monument, Bring a tent and a good attitude

No drugs/alcohol
No violence
No discrimination
633477090033654.name: The July 4th Million Mask Occupation of Washington D.C.

642321105815732.description:
Thirje për demonstratë

Shoqatat shqiptare me origjinë nga trojet tona etnike në Mal të Zi, me veprimtari në SHBA,të bashkuara si asnjëherë tjetër më parë,ju bëjnë thirrje që të merrni pjesë në demonstratën,që do të organizohet në Washington DC me datën 8 Prill 2014, me rastin e vizitës të kryeministrit malazias Gjukanoviq. Demonstrata do të mbahet para Shtëpisë së Bardhë me fillim në orën 10am dhe ambasadës së Malit të Zi në orën 12pm.
Shoqatat:
Shoqata “Ana e Malit” New York;
Shoqata “Dedë Gjon Luli” New York;
Fondacioni “Dom Simon Filipaj” New York;
Fondacioni “Plavë-Guci” New York;
Fondi humanitar “Malësia “ New York;
Shoqata atdhetare “Malësia e madhe” Detroit;
Shoqata atdhetare “Kraja” New York;
Shoqata “Ulqini” Çikago;
“Rrënjët Shqiptare”.
I bëjmë thirrje komunitetit shqiptar të SHBA-së,Ligës Qytetare Shqiptaro-Amerikane, Këshillit Shqiptaro-Amerikan,Organizatës Panshqiptare “ Vatra “ Shoqatës Rugova dhe gjithë shoqatave me origjinë nga trojet tona etnike me veprimtari në SHBA, që ta përkrahin këtë demonstratë, të marrin pjesë masive dhe të solidarizohen me vëllezërit tanë që gjinden në Malin e Zi ! Kjo demonstratë organizohet, për të ngritur zërin e protestës kundër politikës diskriminuese, të cilën aparati shtetëror malazias ushtron vazhdimisht kundër bashkëkombasve tanë në vendlindje.
Kjo gjendje pasqyrohet më së miri brenda poezisë së poetit tonë Hajredin Kovaci.
Gojë kemi e nuk flasim
Sy kemi e nuk shohim
Hund kemi e të keqen nuk e nuhasim
Vesh kemi e nuk ndigjojmë
Fytyrë kemi e disa vënë maska
Këmbë kemi e s’lëvizim dot nga vendi
Duar kemi e sbëjmë me gisht
Zemër kemi e frigën në palc
Të gjitha i kemi e në heshtje po zhdukemi.

Me këtë rast u bëjmë thirje të gjithë shqiptarëve që ti përgjigjen në mënyrë masive kësaj demonstrate, sepse vetëm kështu do të merret vesht se vëllezërit tanë në vendlindje po përjetojnë një diskriminim të nivelit të lartë. Është koha që më në fund ta ngrisim zërin kundër regjimit totalitar të Gjukanoviqit, i cili në takimin në Washington vjen për të fituar përkrahjen e SHBA-ve, për integrimet euro-atlantike. E kemi obligim kombëtar, që të pengojmë inkuadrimin e Malit të Zi në Europ, pa u dhënë të drejtat, të cilat i takojnë pakicës autoktone shqiptare.
Është koha kur politikës dhe strategjisë së dyfishtë të shtetit të Malit të Zi, ti dilet përpara me demonstratë masive.

Nisja bëhet në mënyrë te organizuar me autobus në ora 4:30am prej Staten Island, vendi i takimit do të jetë në South Beach boardwalk parking lot në rrugën Father Capodanno Blvd pranë Restaurantit Vanderbillt.
Per rezervimin e vendeve në autobus si dhe për çdo informatë në lidhje me organizimin e demonstratës mund të kontaktoni në numrat e telefonave;I. Kurti (347) 723 5016, A. Llunja (917) 417 7498, Xh. Zeneli (917) 470 7325, F. Kallaba (917) 692 1939, Z. Kraja (917) 502 5039. ,
Në Bronx, Arthur ave para lokalit të Gjergj Dedvukaj “Giovanni”në orën 4am, kontaktoni Agim Rugova 917 291 0138 dhe Fahredin Kukaj 201 304 1113 dhe në Brooklyn në kryqezimin Church dhe McDonald, në orën 4am , Mustaf Ahmetaj 917 548 6273
Detroit- Nisja behet ne mënyrë te organizuar me autobus , nga oborri i Kishës së Shën Palit në Rochester Hills, ditën e Hënë, me 7 Prill, 2014, në ora 8 të mbrëmjes.
Për rezervimin e vendeve ju lutemi telefononi: 586-530-0373 dhe 586-929-9062.
Apelojmë tek të gjithë të interesuarit që ti bëjnë rezervimet për udhëtimin me autobus sa më shpejt.
Me respekt,
Këshilli organizativ i demonstratës.

642698999109124.description:
You are invited!  Join us for the LAUNCH of this groundbreaking new event created and designed for diverse aspiring lawyers and leaders!

The National Diversity Pre-Law Conference and Law Fair's inaugural event will take place on Friday and Saturday, April 4th and April 5th, 2014 at The Washington Court Hotel on Capitol Hill in Washington, DC - conveniently located just minutes walking distance from the U.S. Capitol and the Supreme Court of the United States.

This event will address what diverse law school admissions candidates can do to be more competitive and strategic candidates.  Even more, it will cover the tough issues surrounding diversity in law school admission, in the law school environment and in the legal profession.  

We will honestly discuss the harsh realities of the changing legal market, the down economy and the current state of legal education.  We want to help diverse aspiring lawyers to better understand the very real obstacles and challenges ahead in law school, in the job search and in the legal profession that could hold them back from being successful if they are unaware of and not ready to take them on.  We want to provide them with tools and strategies to be the very best admissions candidates, law students and lawyers that they can be. 

Further, we want to encourage them to become leaders in the area of diversity so that they will take on and continue the critical work in their law schools and legal work environments to help make them more diverse and inclusive.  The legal profession has been slow to change and lags behind others in maintaining and increasing diversity.  We believe that we all have a role in making meaningful change.

We aim to give conference attendees access to information, resources and contacts that can help better position them to succeed BEFORE they begin the admissions process or even start law school.  Further, we will impress upon them the importance of not only making a living, but also making a difference.  We will make them aware of opportunities to serve the community and of their social responsibility to have a positive impact on society.

This conference will provide:

* Workshops and Panels
* Keynote Speakers
* Training/Seminars
* Law School Recruitment Fair
* Diversity Resources Fair
* Scheduled Group Visits to the U.S. Capitol and the Supreme Court of the United States
* Community Service Opportunity

ALL law schools and organizations that provide programs or services targeting diverse prospective law students are invited to participate.  

Who represents diversity?  Different cultural and social identity groups including: Native Americans, African Americans/Blacks, Asian Pacific Americans, Hispanics/Latinos, Women, Disabled, Sexual Orientation/Gender Identity (LGBT), and Age/Non-Traditional Status.

We welcome all pre-law students (high school students, college students, college graduates, career changers, working professionals), multicultural/diversity administrators, law students, law graduates, lawyers, law school administrators, law professors, judges, etc.

If you are a law student, lawyer, bar leader, or diversity professional and you are interested in being involved with this event, please send an e-mail to info@diversityprelawconference.org.

THIS EVENT IS OPEN TO THE PUBLIC AND COMPLETELY FREE OF CHARGE!

EVERYONE IS WELCOME TO ATTEND!  SPACES ARE LIMITED!

Ultimately we hope to provide participants with opportunities to learn not only about law school and the legal profession, but more about the critical areas of:
* Diversity and Inclusion 
* Coalition Building 
* Cultural Competence 
* Leadership 
* Professionalism 
* Service 
* Social Responsibility
* Social Justice

REGISTRATION IS FREE!
