Now since I have everything lined up, I'd like to announce that I have planned a bus trip on May 10, 2014 to the National Zoo in Washington DC.  The cost PER PERSON (from birth to 125 lo, as the price is to reserve a seat on the busl) is $31. This price is for THE BUS ONLY and your seat will not be reserved until I have cash in my hand. We will be departing promptly at 7am on that morning from the parking lot of my husbands work, (I can provide address and/or directions at a later time). And returning no later than 10pm, as long as traffic cooperates.
Admission to the zoo is free. The bus will drop off near the gate and will pick everyone back up at the designated time.  You are free to roam DC, you are not restricted to be within the confines of the National Zoo. You may do your own thing as long as you return in time to board the bus back to NJ. If you miss the bus, I hope you have train fare or comfortable shoes. It will be a long walk back home. 
Upon departure from the Zoo, we will be stopping for dinner in Essex, Maryland at Cactus Willies Steak Buffet for dinner. I have made a group reservation to assure they can accomodate us. The dinner price for adults is $14.29 + 0.75 gratuity totalling $15.04. There is a discount for seniors as well as children. What the discount is, I do not know. Their website is cactuswillies.com if you would like more information. I have eaten there a few times, it is a nice place and the food is good. 
I will also be holding a 50/50 raffle on the bus as we travel south, one half to be given to our driver as his tip and the other half to go to some lucky winner.
Anything you bring with you, I would recommend taking with you as we exit the bus to enter the zoo, as Sheppard Bus Company is NOT liable for anything lost or stolen from the bus. The bus will also have on an board dvd player ans several monitors if anyone would like to bring a dvd or two to share and make the ride a little more bearable for the children in attendance.
If you are interested in going, please contact me and make arrangements for payment to reserve your seat(s).
THIS TRIP IS IN NO WAY SPONSORED OR ENDORSED BY ANY BUSINESS, GROUP OR IS IT IN ANY WAY, ANY TYPE OF FUNDRAISER. 
I am hoping by word of mouth, we will fill the bus and have a great time at the zoo.

657809960946074.description:
What is your only comfort in life and death?

This question was raised during the Reformation, when many Protestants sought and found Christian comfort through the rediscovery of a biblical vision of assurance of one's salvation, secured by Christ alone through faith alone. The Reformers feared that medieval forms of Christian piety too often were motivated by doubt of one's salvation, and fear about the coming judgment. Roman Catholic piety, in contrast, emphasized that Christian comfort is experienced through the sacramental life of the church, penitential practices and pilgrimages, and the veneration and mediation of Mary and the Saints. The Roman Church taught that the simplicity of Protestant piety cut the believer off from an abundance of practical supports.

Presenters Dr. Brian Lee, Pastor of Christ Reformed, and Barrett Turner, a doctoral candidate at the Catholic University of America, will present Protestant and Catholic positions on the topic and field audience questions. A casual pizza dinner will be served (RSVP Required), and the event will be jointly presented by Christ Reformed Church, Washington DC and "Faith Discussion Dinner." Please visit www.faithdiscussion.org/home/nextdiscussion.html for more information.

RSVP required for FREE "We the Pizza" dinner. Please RSVP via Facebook or through the Faith Discussion link.
657809960946074.name: How Does Faith Comfort You? A Protestant & Catholic Discussion

Manufactured Superstars


Thursday April 10, 2014

Doors 10PM | No dress code | Ages 18+
Ultrabar • 911 F Street NW • Washington, DC  

You’re not dreaming. This is real. The club you’re in feels as though the entire building is the VIP area, not just because of the lingerie models wearing black nerd-glasses piling over you to reach another bottle of bubbly, or the gyrating wall-to-wall moshpit that’s the dancefloor. Tonight feels special because the DJs – the engine of the party – are rockin’ it like you’ve never imagined. Oh, and they’re wearing matching NASA spacesuits and there’s a six-foot-tall teddy bear onstage hyping the crowd like a maniacal MC. The DJs are MANUFACTURED SUPERSTARS, and tonight is every night.

MANUFACTURED SUPERSTARS are BRADLEY ROULIER and SHAWN SABO. As DJs, their performance style is as high-energy, accessible and fun as it is technically challenging. Although their DJ performances have been described as “mash-up” or “open-format” by many in the music press, what they really do is create a non-stop tornado of happiness when they spin. This can be evidenced by the countless smiling faces in their crowds and the consistently sold-out shows.

The MANUFACTURED SUPERSTARS have long been technologically savvy, and technology coexists organically in their everyday lives. ROULIER is a co-founder and founding member of leading digital music retailer, BEATPORT.COM. SABO was an original employee of BEATPORT and he remains a member.

665377400175493.description:
Onward and Upward Travel Club: elegant escorted luxury trips featuring fashion, food, art, culture, and chocolate. 

Experience a springtime jaunt through DC, as Club Founder Valerie Beck opens her address book and takes us to top spots with local cultural creators. 

Pillar of the trip: the annual Cherry Blossom Festival. We'll participate through art, a tree tour with a National Ranger, and a kimono trunk show. We'll pick up on the Calder exhibition in Los Angeles - which we will have seen on our trip earlier this year - with a visit to one of Calder's grandest artworks at the National Gallery in DC, and add a wine and chocolate tasting to the mix with a local celebrity pastry chef as we welcome spring in our nation's capital. 

2 nights, Friday 4/4/14 - Sunday 4/6/14, Hotel Monaco DC.

693565997357024.description:
Gallup and Meridian International Center are pleased to invite you to the launch of the latest global insight into the standing of U.S. leadership in the eyes of the world. “What the World Thinks about U.S. Leadership” will take place April 10, 2014, from 8:30 am to 10:00 am, with registration and a light breakfast beginning at 8:00 am at The Gallup Building, 901 F St NW, Washington, DC. Please note that the entrance to The Gallup Building is on Ninth Street.
 
The event will include insight from Ambassador Stuart W. Holliday, President and CEO, Meridian International Center, in addition to a high-level panel discussion with H.E. Igor Munteanu, Ambassador of the Republic of Moldova to the U.S. and H.E. Adebowale Ibibapo Adefuye, Ambassador of the Federal Republic of Nigeria to the U.S. The discussion and Q&A to follow will enable public- and private-sector leaders to better understand what is driving global views of U.S. leadership, create a context for collaboration on how to improve those views, and enhance U.S. public and private global engagement efforts.
 
Mr. Jon Clifton, Managing Director, Gallup World Poll will introduce the event with a presentation of Gallup's latest World Poll, which surveys more than 150 countries that are home to more than 98% of the world's population, with specific insight into: global approval trends of U.S. leadership from the Bush administration to the Obama administration; analysis of the countries with highest and lowest approval of U.S. leadership, and U.S. standing vs. other world leadership; analysis for each major global region -- the Americas, Europe, Africa, and Asia; and the effect of U.S. foreign policy on global opinion.
 
Based on more than 1,000 country studies and seven years of data collection, the U.S.-Global Leadership Project is a joint effort to provide a comprehensive assessment of how the global community views U.S. leadership.
 
Registration is required at: https://registration.gallup.com/?O=FZC1115AJQ740223RS. For more information, please contact Heather Haines at 202-939-5570.

693565997357024.name: What the World Thinks about U.S. Leadership with H.E. Igor Munteanu

709164649147184.description:
With the confluence of low-cost, high-speed internet and access to mobile telephony, the Africa region is increasingly producing companies that are active contributors to global technology innovation.  Whether its in the humanitarian and emergency response domain(Ushahidi) or commercial(iRoko Partners, Jumia, MPesa), or the entrance of leading companies such IBM, Microsoft, and Google who have set up offices on the continent, tech innovation has firmly become part of the African narrative.

Come join us for three days and three events, where you will experience what the continent and Diaspora innovators have to offer.

Lineup of Events:
April 26th - Hackathon for Revisionprep
Time: 10AM April 26th -9:59AM April 27th
Description: 
We want to encourage collaboration between students, artists, and software consultants, engineers, international development professional and anybody else interested in creating transformative education technology for Africa. Tiphub & Mansa Colabs aim to catalyze the innovation in Africa and the African diaspora by supporting developers and applications that address community needs, while demonstrating to local leaders and decision makers how mobile technologies can lead to the next generation of tech jobs and investment.

RevisionPrep, an African Diaspora youth lead venture, is developing a gamified online social learning tool that offers an alternative to traditional exam preparation in Ghanaian Junior High Schools for the national Basic Education Certificate Examination (BECE). Every ninth grade student in Junior High School seeking admission to public Senior High Schools in Ghana is required to take the BECE. Based on performance on the exam, students are placed into specific high schools in the country.

Hackathon Prompt:
Using a cross-disciplinary set of teams, attendees will assist RevisionPrep identify opportunities/challenges in market size, think through curriculum materials, user-experience and/or back-end data collection needs.
 
April 27th - Site launch for Africandevjobs.com
Time: 6:30pm-8pm
Description:
AfricanDevJobs.com connects organizations and people who are focused on Africa’s growth and development. Through employment opportunities and career advancement resources for professionals, the organization is committed to social and economic development in Africa.  The social enterprise provides a platform for recruitment, networking, and information in African development.

This launch event is open to African development professionals, employers, and enthusiasts. There will be a demo of the new online platform that is making African development career exploration easier and the founder will also be present to answer your questions.  

April 28th - Fireside Chat with Enyo Kumahor, Managing Director ThoughtWorks Africa
Time: 6:30pm-8pm
Description:
Betty Enyonam Kumahor is the Regional Managing Director of Pan-Africa for ThoughtWorks, a global IT consulting firm. Nominated as Best African Company of the Year 2013 by African Business Awards, ThoughtWorks has already made a marked impact on the continent with a diverse portfolio of clients including some of the largest, most innovative, and socially impactful organisations on the continent.

Enyo joined ThoughtWorks from Ernst & Young where she led the led Ernst & Young’s Service Delivery Technology function for their Global Advisory practice deploying technology solutions across the 140+ countries where Ernst & Young operates. Enyo also expanded their IT and Program Advisory Services practices for Ernst & Young in West Africa, building a multi-million dollar practice providing program advisory, IT audit, IT risk management, IT transformation and outsourcing advisory services to clients spanning multiple industries including telecommunications, financial services, as well as government and public sector.

723821267669024.description:
ELENA will have two screenings in DC on Saturday, May 10, hosted by the West End Cinema and Bloombars, with support of the Embassy of Brazil in Washington, DC:

* 3:00 pm, West End Cinema
* Special guest: Professor Regina Igel, University of Maryland

* 7:30 pm, Bloombars
* Special guest: Professor Renato Alvim, American University)

Both screenings are FREE, and will be followed with Q&As with director Petra Costa and her guests.

For more information, contact Roberta Alves at
roalves.zeroii@gmail.com or 202-352-5623. 

About the Film: 

From executive producers Tim Robbins and Fernando Meirelles, one of the most successful documentaries of all time in Brazil now comes to America. Intimate in style, ELENA delves into the abyss of one familyʼs drama, revealing at once the inspiration that can be born from tragedy. 

Elena, a young Brazilian woman, moves to New York with the same dream her mother had: to become a movie actress. She leaves behind her childhood spent in hiding during the years of the military dictatorship. She also leaves Petra, her seven-year-old sister. The calls and letters trail off, until one day they stop entirely. Two decades later, Petra also becomes an actress and heads to New York. At first in search of her destiny, but increasingly, in search of Elena, Petra has only a few clues: home movies, newspaper clippings, a diary and some letters. Despite the long odds, at any moment, Petra hopes to find Elena walking in the streets. 

Gradually, the features of the two sisters are confused; we no longer know one from the other. When Petra finally finds Elena in an unexpected place, she has to learn to let her go. ELENA is a film about the persistence of those memories, the irreversibility of that loss, and the impact the absence of her sister had on the seven year-old girl3
723821267669024.name: ELENA in Washington, DC

729416170423156.description:
The countdown begins, friends.  The date has been set, and I am leaving you all for California on Saturday, April 12th.

The sad thing is, I haven't really gotten to experience that much of DC, seeing as I've only lived here for 8 months and all.  So before I go, I want to make sure I get to see and experience the best DC has to offer.  Therefore, I would like you to help me create a bucket list, to be completed on or before Friday night, my last night here with you.

The rules?  The items on the list can't cost too much, because I'm bankrolling a bicoastal move on a teacher's salary.  Also, nothing TOO incriminating; I do anticipate a future in which they will still allow me to work with children.  Other than that, be creative, be kind.  Favorite foods?  Experiences?  Museums?  Bars?  Lay 'em on me.  I will even take suggestions as to where to have a goodbye shindig.

735459373152475.description:
Join D.C. System Change Not Climate for a screening and discussion of the documentary Bidder70.

Bidder 70 centers on an extraordinary, ingenious and effective act of civil disobedience demanding government and industry accountability. In 2008, University of Utah economics student Tim DeChristopher committed an act which would redefine patriotism in our time, igniting a spirit of civil disobedience in the name of climate justice.

On December 19, 2008 Tim DeChristopher disrupted a highly disputed Utah BLM Oil and Gas lease auction, effectively safeguarding thousands of acres of pristine Utah land that were slated for oil and gas leases. Not content to merely protest outside, Tim entered the auction hall and registered as bidder #70. He outbid industry giants on land parcels (which, starting at $2 an acre, were adjacent to national treasures like Canyonlands National Park), winning 22,000 acres of land worth $1.7 million before the auction was halted.

Two months later, incoming Interior Secretary Ken Salazar invalidated the auction. DeChristopher, however, was indicted on two federal felonies with penalties of up to 10 years in prison and $750,000 in fines. Patrick Shea, former BLM Director for Clinton, represented DeChristopher pro-bono.

With the threat of prison looming, DeChristopher stepped up his activism and evolved into a charismatic and ingenious climate justice leader. He co-founded Peaceful Uprising, a grass-roots group dedicated to defending a livable future through empowering non-violent action.

After two years and nine postponements, his trial began on February 28, 2011. Outside the courtroom, hundreds rallied in solidarity with Tim. Inside, Judge Dee Benson disallowed every defense his lawyers put forth. After a five-day trial, DeChristopher was found guilty. His sentencing was scheduled for summer 2011.

Refusing to back down, Tim flew to D.C. in April 2011 to give a keynote speech at Power Shift 2011 in front of 10,000 students. He then led students to occupy the Department of the Interior. Tim wisely avoided arrest, but dozens of others were arrested for this mass act of peaceful civil disobedience.

On July 26th Tim was sentenced to two years in federal prison and removed immediately from court in chains.

Sponsored by:
D.C. System Change Not Climate Change, 
Defending Dissent Foundation, 
D.C. Statehood Green Party, 
Metro D.C. Committee of Correspondence for Democracy and Ecosocialism, 
D.C. Metro Science for the People.

Overview:
1. Automaidan @ British and Russsian Embassies
2. “Chain of Freedom” around the White House
3. Walk to Lincoln Memorial - ????
4. Flashmob
5. Ukraine Consulate representatives and US Congress representatives talking about current affairs in Ukraine
6. Media interviews and live stream to Kyiv, Ukraine (also at the White House)
7. Signatures for letters to Barack Obama, Congress and UK Consulate

PLEASE HELP US SPREAD THE WORD ABOUT THIS EVENT!  

In this difficult time for Ukraine, it is of outmost importance for all patriots to unite around one goal—protection and support of our Motherland.

We are extremely grateful for everything you have done and continue to do for our Ukraine, and we would like to share out next project with you:

“THE WORLD UNITED AROUND THE WHITE HOUSE IN SUPPORT OF UKRAINE.” The purpose of this event is to have an elaborate performance allegorizing Ukraine reaching out to the world and offering peace to anyone who dreams of a world without war and tyranny.
The event will start with a procession of cars and buses from New York, New Jersey, Pennsylvania and Connecticut driving by the Russian and British consulates in DC. After this, AutoMaidan NY will join the Ukrainian community and friends of Ukraine by the White House. Here, we plan to form “Chain of Freedom.” Participants will carry an oversized Ukrainian flag and posters. We will chant slogans contending war and Russian occupation of Ukraine, and demanding harsher and more expansive actions taken against Russian officials by the President and his Administration.

The next part of the rally will consist of a walk to Lincoln Memorial, where we will perform a flash mob by forming “UA.” After this, the representatives of Ukrainian Consulate General and US officials will have an opportunity to address the public, and express their support and further actions regarding Ukraine. We will end this rally with singing the national Anthem.
The organizers are inviting various Ukrainian, American and other media outlets to the event, as well as setting up a live stream of the event to Kyiv. We will also collect signatures to accompany a letter to the President and the Congress, as well as the British Consulate, urging them to act in accordance with the Budapest Memorandum (1994), and take decisive and harsh measures in defending the territorial integrity of Ukraine, and preventing further Russian aggression.

We are asking you for your support in spreading the word about this rally to friends and media. 

Those who do not have a car or do not wish to drive to Washington will be able to register for a seat on a bus (details forthcoming) or with a fellow goer (please see the link to registration document in the top portion of the post).

Those of you who do have an extra seat or two,and would be kind enough to take someone with you, PLEASE refer to the same document. 

THANK YOU! Slava Ukrajini! Glory to Ukraine!

792381887456344.description:
At 4:20pm every day during the early 1970s, a group of teens in San Rafael, California went to a wall outside of school grounds to smoke pot. They called their afternoon toke “420,” but never envisioned the code word becoming a worldwide phenomenon.

These days, hundreds of thousands of stoners across the globe celebrate April 20th like it’s marijuana Christmas. In the United States, Washington, D.C., doubles as America’s cannabis capital come 420 Day.

420 Day Washington, D.C. 2014 is chock-full of 420 Day celebrations like Overgrow the Government National 4/20 Rally 2014. There, hemp lovers unite and rally, urging bureaucrats to reconsider their years-long pot prohibition.

High, patriotic protestors can roam the National Mall to come up with their own theories as to whether or not the area is steeped in hidden Masonic code. Blazed Dan Browns are free to stop in one of the 10 Smithsonian museums along the park’s outer edges, where they’ll find plenty of visual stimulation.

Though pot might not be legal quite yet in America’s capital, 420 Day events in Washington, D.C., rival those in any other American city, or any city in the world for that matter. Whether you smoke up, down, or out, there’s no doubt you’ll have a blast at 420 Day Washington, D.C., 2014.
792381887456344.name: 420 Day Washington, D.C. 2014

The Ringling Bros. circus is coming to Washington DC! Please join local PETA supporters to rally against the use of animals in circuses. 

Thursday, March 20, 12 noon–1 p.m. and 6:30–7:30 p.m. 
Friday, March 21, 9:30-10:30 a.m. and 6:30-7:30 p.m. 
Saturday, March 22, 10:30-11:30 a.m., 2:30-3:30 p.m., and 6:30-7:30 p.m. 
Sunday, March 23, 10:30-11:30 a.m., 2:30-3:30 p.m., and 6:30-7:30 p.m.

Verizon Center

Materials will be provided.

Elephants in Ringling's possession are chained inside filthy, poorly ventilated boxcars for an average of more than 26 straight hours—and often 60 to 70 hours at a time—when the circus travels. Even former Ringling employees have reported that elephants are routinely abused and violently beaten with bullhooks (an elephant-training tool that resembles a fireplace poker), in order to force them to perform tricks.

To learn more about how animals suffer behind the scenes at Ringling, check out RinglingBeatsAnimals.com

Echevarria Travel is once again doing a bus trip to Washington DC - Columbus Day Weekend - October 10-13, 2014.

Pricing: $419 per person double occupancy, call for pricing on singles and triples.  Children over the age of 8 will be allowed, but no discount for children.  Checks will be made out to Echevarria Travel in the memo for Washington, DC Trip.

For Single Occupancy add on $120 per person.

Deposits of $75 due no later than June 20th, 2014 and final payment due no later than July 20th, 2014

Itinerary as follows

We will be departing Brentwood, NY at 8AM and depending on traffic at 135 West 23rd street, New York, 10011, between 6th and 7th avenues between 9-10AM.

What is included in this incredible Price:

• Motorcoach Transportation (included in needed Wheelchair lift for people permanently in wheelchairs.)

• 3 Nights Lodging (hotel has not be decided yet, but the company uses such hotels as Holiday Inn, Best Western, and similar)

• 6 Meals: Breakfast and Dinner

o World Word II Memorial

o Capital Hill

o Embassy Row

o The Korean War Veterans Memorial

o The Vietnam Veterans Memorial

o The Smithsonian

o The Martin Luther King, Jr. National Memorial

o The Lincoln Memorial and more!

• Two full-day Guided Tours of Washington, DC

• Evening Guided Memorial and Monument Tour

• Tips for Motorcoach Drive and Step-On Guides

Day 1: Depart your group's location in a spacious video and restroom equipped motorcoach as you head for your destination: Washington, D.C. our National Capital! Later that day, enjoy a relaxing Dinner and check into your Washington, D.C. area hotel.

Day 2: Enjoy a Continental Breakfast before departing for a full-day Guided Tour of Washington, D.C. Some of the awe-inspiring sights on this fantastic tour will include the US Capitol, the White House, the National Archives, Embassy Row, and Georgetown. During the day, you will see the Washington Monument, Lincoln Memorial, the Martin Luther King, Jr. National Memorial, and several War Memorials. This evening, enjoy Dinner at a local restaurant before continuing on the Guided Memorial and Monuments Tour.

Day 3: Begin the day with a Continental Breakfast. Today's Guided Tour includes such poignant and inspirational sights as Arlington National Cemetery, including the Tomb of the Unknowns, and Kennedy Graves, as well as the Iwo Jima Memorial. You'll also enjoy a visit to the Smithsonian Institution. Later, you'll enjoy Dinner with entertainment before returning to your hotel for the night. If you would like to go to the Holocaust Museum instead of the Smithsonian (we will be here for 4 hours), it is a free museum and is 4 blocks away.  That you can do on your own.

Day 4: Today, after enjoying a Continental Breakfast, you will depart for home... a perfect time to chat with your friends about all the fun things you’ve done, the great sights you’ve seen, and where your next group trip will take you!

Payment options check or money order made out to Echevarria Travel and mailed to:

You are invited to attend a special presentation by Pastor Steve Khoury from Bethlehem this Wednesday, March 26 at 7 p.m. (Living Word's Wednesday night service.)

Pastor Khoury is a frequent speaker at CUFI's Washington, D.C. Annual Summit. He and his father are among the very few Palestinian Christians who support Israel. His father, Dr. Naim Khoury, had established a ministry in 1980. Today they are spreading the gospel throughout the Palestinian Territories and in Jerusalem, he pastors Calvary Baptist Church.

Ilan Sharon, our Israeli Jewish friend will join us as well to share about the special relationship he has with Pastor Khoury.

IMPORTANT NOTE for attendees who are not Living Word members: The presentation is part of Living Word's weekly Wednesday night service and will include Christian Praise and Worship in the first 15 minutes and the message from Pastor Khoury is a strong message of Christian faith, however, we believe it is great source of education to anyone that is interested in Israel and the story of the Christian minority living in Palestinian controlled area.

The Church has (as part of their regular Wednesday night service) Christian childcare for newborns thru 5th grade. The sanctuary also has balcony area which is great for families.
 
What: A Taste of CUFI's Washington, D.C. Summit 
 Story of Faith at Work in the Little Town of Bethlehem 
with Pastor Steve Khoury from Bethlehem (bio enclosed below)

When: 7 p.m., Wednesday, March 26, 2014
 
Where: Main Sanctuary
Living Word Christian Center
9201 75th Avenue N.
Brooklyn Park, MN
(12 minutes North from 394 & 169)

For map or directions either call (763) 315-7000 or click: http://bitly.com/1b8Pnym

RSVP is NOT required.

BRIEF BIO, Pastor Steve Khoury:
 
Growing up with daily persecution, Steven Khoury has seen church members attacked, subjected to discrimination, and lose their income all because of their faith. Several believers under his ministry have been martyred, including his own uncle, and several youth girls who invited children to vacation bible school. Persecution has always faced Pastor Khoury's life growing up as an Arab pastor during the intifadas.
 
Pastor Steven Khoury is the Vice President of Holy Land Missions, which has been reaching out to the lost in Israel for the past 30 years. Today, six locations around the country are actively serving the community and preaching the Gospel, including Calvary Church in Jerusalem and First Baptist in Bethlehem.
 
Pastor Khoury attended Bible College in Springfield, Missouri, where he received his Bachelor of Science in Pastoral Ministry and Theology. He is an affiliate with the Baptist Bible Fellowship International, the National Christian Foundation, and the Voice of the Martyrs Organization. He is the youngest ordained Israeli Arab pastor in Israel and the surrounding Arab countries.
 
Pastor Khoury is author of the book, Diplomatic Christianity: Standing in the Shadow of Tomorrow's Persecution. His ministry has been a topic in several books. Steven has also done numerous interviews, including recent broadcasts on FOX News and CBN.

869422266417285.description:
The Get Right Band Rocks Solly's in DC! Come on out and shake something!

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xEgJmc6IYaY

The Get Right Band:

One of Relix Magazine’s “On The Verge” picks, THE GET RIGHT BAND is “hip-shaking, earthquaking pure funk fun” (The Alternate Root). Combining catchy, clever songwriting with musical expertise and fearless improvisation, the live show promises to make you shake everything you’ve got. From funk to rock n’ roll to reggae, this is a dance party. This is an ass shaking good time.

“The Get Right Band is a three-piece with the musical energy and power of The Police,” says Rock and Roll Hall of Famer and legendary Lynyrd Skynyrd drummer Artimus Pyle. The Transylvania Times writes that the band “takes the stage with a palpable sense of energy.”

The band is built on the musical brotherhood that guitarist/vocalist Silas Durocher and bassist Jesse Gentry have formed playing music together since middle school. With the addition of Jian-Claude Mears, a powerful and dynamic drummer, the group’s sound has become an unstoppable force. The Get Right Band has been touring the East Coast and the Caribbean heavily since their inception in April, 2011. The band has rocked hard and jammed relentlessly every step of the way.

The Get Right Band’s debut CD, Shake, was released in February, 2013. Hittin’ The Note Magazine says the disc is “fun, full of energy and excitement, and should be listened to with the volume turned all the way up.” The rock n’ roll album features stripped down but creatively layered and produced performances of the band’s original tunes. It’s “groove with rock melodies built on funk attitudes,” says The Mountain Xpress. From the seductive blues of “Voodoo Doll” to the dance party vibe of “Chromaticize” to the Caribbean influenced “Touch The Holy,” (inspired by the band’s Caribbean tours) Shake’s “impressive stylistic range manages to all fit within the band’s distinctive image” (WNC Magazine). The Grateful Web writes that the disc is a “tasty mix of hip-swinging selections that leaves the listener thirsty for more.”

The members of The Get Right Band have played with many of the East Coast’s greatest acts, including Laura Reed and Deep Pocket, Woody Wood, Josh Phillips, The Artimus Pyle Band, Scrappy Hamilton (now Truth & Salvage Company), Afromotive, and Royal Trux (Virgin Records), and have shared the stage with national acts such as Galactic, Victor Wooten Band, Mike Dillon Band, Jeff Sipe Trio, Yo Mama’s Big Fat Booty Band, Jeff Coffin’s Mutet, Larry Keel, and Bobby Lee Rodgers.

Website: www.thegetrightband.com
